


translate English day4_my_8358f928:


    br "\n I still remember what the angel's face looked like, though I probably shouldn't know.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_my_0e8a72ca:


    extend "\nAnd as proof of that, my memories and thoughts stop short of knowing who she actually is.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_my_87d56ec2:


    extend " Every time I try to conjure up an image of her, something seems to block me from doing so.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_my_59fa5c88:


    extend " I'm sure this is a test from her to see what I'll do. If she is a real person, then she probably doesn't know she's an angel.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_my_8027fdbc:


    extend "So she wants me to try and find her, which is why she keeps appearing to me in my dreams.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_my_1e0dcddd:


    extend "\nOr perhaps it's something different.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_my_8331b60a:


    extend " Maybe this unidentified person's appearance in my dreams in the form of an angel is a type of warning--the kind that means something might happen once I discover her real identity."


translate English day4_my_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day4_my_26105621:


    nar "On edge, I head to the garden. I find her standing next to rose arbor, a heavy-looking pair of scissors in her hands."


translate English day4_my_886abf09:


    nar "I heard that Maya had made it back safe, but seeing her here, safely in the garden, sends a rush of relief through my body."


translate English day4_my_b904a3de:


    nar "It seems like she's in a bad mood, though. When I raise my hand in greeting, she merely gives a single shake of her head without turning to acknowledge me."


translate English day4_my_f2d5cd26:


    nar "Her gaze remains focused on the roses."


translate English day4_my_832253bd:


    pl "Where did you get those scissors from, Maya?"


translate English day4_my_3334fc23:


    my "..."


translate English day4_my_7d412959:


    nar "She moves the clippers open and shut as she silently considers her answer, her eyes moving to and fro in thought."


translate English day4_my_0e97dc24:


    nar "The scissors, which could be considered a deadly weapon, seem extra sharp in contrast to Maya's slender arms. "


translate English day4_my_d82a2405:


    nar "Yet she handles them easily, the blades coming together with sharp snipping sounds."


translate English day4_my_9e63839b:


    my "Actually... the bishop was just here a moment ago."


translate English day4_my_84f4df10:


    pl "Huh? Did you get in trouble for going to the Academic's Department?"


translate English day4_my_c0c7aef3:


    nar "She shakes her head."


translate English day4_my_e17df931:


    my "This garden... it used to belong to the bishop. I wasn't in trouble or anything, though... she just told me a few things."


translate English day4_my_351da2ee:


    pl "Oh, yeah? Well, that's good. It seems just like her to enjoy tending a garden."


translate English day4_my_dd3bf083:


    my "It's true..."


translate English day4_my_6a9a35fa:


    nar "She glances away again and I follow her gaze to see that the roses look different than usual. "


translate English day4_my_d359dcf3:


    nar "A bunch of the stray branches have been trimmed, exposing a pure-white center."


translate English day4_my_3affdf64:


    nar "Maya's probably searching for any stems that need trimming."


translate English day4_my_76bf61f3:


    pl "All the roses here are bright red."


translate English day4_my_25d9feda:


    my "They have a name. "


translate English day4_my_e6ccad4d:


    my "They're called Scarlet Meidiland. Only self-sustaining flowers that can handle the cold that prevades the capital can thrive here... or so I've heard."


translate English day4_my_2915c731:


    pl "Wow, I didn't realize there were different types of roses."


translate English day4_my_63911daf:


    my "It has the most variants out of any other flower. "


translate English day4_my_dbdf6703:


    my "Although vestis caused various living organisms to lose their homes, this rose in particular still manages to flourish...somehow."


translate English day4_my_fb15b52d:


    my "There are plenty of other vegetation and flowers that continue to thrive,"


translate English day4_my_27f064ba:


    my "and yet roses are the strongest due to their natural brilliance and fragrant perfume..."


translate English day4_my_03e25be1:


    my "...Th-That's just what I've heard...at least."


translate English day4_my_11cd2f4f:


    pl "Oh, crap! Sorry for staring. You always get way more energetic when talking about flowers."


translate English day4_my_0716f848:


    my "Flowers...? Well, I do really like living creatures of all types, though... I'm sure it's not interesting to you."


translate English day4_my_6a460956:


    pl "That's not true at all. In fact, I think it's great!"


translate English day4_my_26b3c75b:


    pl "It's not a bad thing to be super knowledgeable when it comes to things that interest you, right? Come to think of it, I don't think there's anything I've devoted myself to..."


translate English day4_my_2350f2c8:


    my "Ah, I've liked them ever since I was young... There's nothing I know nearly as much about..."


translate English day4_my_795fb255:


    my "Everyone else tends to talk about clothes, their future, or romance. I guess I'm pretty strange, huh?"


translate English day4_my_a9b439d7:


    pl "Not strange at all. The bishop must have let you use her scissors because she knows how much you love flowers."


translate English day4_my_aedb9cdc:


    my "Maybe... Liking living creatures and taking care of them are two different things, though."


translate English day4_my_0adbc5f6:


    nar "Snip!!! She brings the sharp blades together again, cleanly cutting through another rose branch."


translate English day4_my_58a932db:


    my "I love flowers a lot, but I've never tried growing or nurturing them..."


translate English day4_my_05d40694:


    my "I tried tending to some morning glories once with my family, but mine were the only ones that refused to bloom before dying."


translate English day4_my_9cad5d17:


    my "And it's not just flowers. Even bugs and fish die in my care as well..."


translate English day4_my_f28d6dc0:


    my "Everything I touch seems to die. It's almost as if..."


translate English day4_my_c3517138:


    pl "You're wrong."


translate English day4_my_c9240539:


    nar "I quickly interrupt her before she can say anything strange again."


translate English day4_my_3df2f2fe:


    pl "There's no way you could kill anything with hands that pretty and a heart so kind."


translate English day4_my_ca2f5337:


    pl "I'm sure it was just bad luck and awful timing."


translate English day4_my_429081fd:


    my "If it really was bad luck then whose luck is to blame? Mine...or theirs?"


translate English day4_my_216b7dc9:


    pl "Theirs, of course! You know how they say one's life expectancy is predetermined the moment they're born?"


translate English day4_my_b17205cb:


    pl "I'm sure the flowers and the fish died according to their lifespan, which is what led to you thinking you're a magnet for bad luck."


translate English day4_my_9d704079:


    pl "There's no possible way you were the victim of bad luck. Got it?"


translate English day4_my_3334fc23_1:


    my "..."


translate English day4_my_a1917c46:


    nar "She nibbles on her lip, looking slightly embarrassed. She must know I'm right."


translate English day4_my_06eee2db:


    pl "You said a requiem for the departed, helping a sinful life be reborn in a new body. Almost like an angel."


translate English day4_my_21b57c6c:


    nar "I'm not exactly sure what significance the word \"angel\" holds in a religious sense, but it seems like a word that holds relevance within the temple."


translate English day4_my_e92aabe9:


    nar "I tried to think up something that might help Maya clear her thoughts a bit, though her expression seems as dark as ever."


translate English day4_my_aa844d17:


    my "An angel...?"


translate English day4_my_61fe5a44:


    pl "You'd think that word might have a more positive connotation, huh?"


translate English day4_my_665edd9a:


    my "Do you think flowers, bugs, and fish can sin?"


translate English day4_my_3e00007b:


    pl "Huh? No, it's more like... they're atoning for the sins they committed in a previous life before becoming an animal."


translate English day4_my_5e734343:


    nar "She blinks at me, almost as if in disbelief of the words coming from my mouth. She's clearly never heard about anything like this before."


translate English day4_my_947caf88:


    pl "That's what everyone says back where I come from. Those who committed the greatest sins are reborn as animals. "


translate English day4_my_d9129659:


    pl "It's almost like by living as a natural creature, you get a chance at a clean slate and your soul is forgiven."


translate English day4_my_ace84c5a:


    my "...Being reborn as an inarticulate animal in order to save my soul sounds kind of like a dream come true."


translate English day4_my_9835a7eb:


    pl "Maya... did something happen?"


translate English day4_my_85fc4976:


    my "No, not really... or at least, I don't think so..."


translate English day4_my_caef4a0a:


    pl "You don't think so? What do you mean?"


translate English day4_my_2c511c91:


    my "There are crimes that weigh heavily against your soul, even without being directly involved... which is why I don't feel I'm able to make that call with full confidence."


translate English day4_my_3e0be26f:


    nar "I decide to keep my mouth shut. Maya gazes off into the distance, clearly thinking about something, before opening her mouth to speak."


translate English day4_my_5f95de9e:


    my "You can't run away from the crimes you've committed."


translate English day4_my_a8be02d6:


    my "No one can take your place... but the role of angels is to lessen the weight of one's karmic retribution."


translate English day4_my_7210bc02:


    my "You reminded me of this fact or perhaps...perhaps you were already aware of it."


translate English day4_my_c6defb03:


    pl "Nope... This is a first for me. We go together so well, Maya. Whenever I talk to you, I always feel so much better after."


translate English day4_my_3faab081:


    my "I feel the same way."


translate English day4_my_4773cd2c:


    my "But, you know... angels, to me, aren't necessarily beacons of virtue..."


translate English day4_my_ff14d760:


    nar "Her words, spoken so softly it's like she's talking to herself, shakes me to my core. "


translate English day4_my_1ac86c99:


    nar "Not beacons of virtue? Then how DOES she view angels?"


translate English day4_my_38f31847:


    nar "As I belatedly begin trying to figure out a way to backtrack, she suddenly turns her head to look at me. "


translate English day4_my_d23219ef:


    nar "My heart throbs almost painfully."


translate English day4_my_3d50f324:


    nar "Fortunately, Maya doesn't seem angry or offended. Instead, it looks like there's a different problem weighing on her mind."


translate English day4_my_a6915d30:


    my "Do you think Cue hates me now?"


translate English day4_my_26e913ea:


    pl "Because of what happened?"


translate English day4_my_db9c913f:


    my "Mm. He was really angry about it..."


translate English day4_my_8a238ec4:


    pl "Even so, I'm the one who acted without thinking things through. I don't think he blames you for what happened."


translate English day4_my_b50aae54:


    my "I just hope we don't have a falling out of sorts..."


translate English day4_my_44bd4aab:


    pl "What do you think about it?"


translate English day4_my_cb627505:


    my "Huh?"


translate English day4_my_c5b6265e:


    pl "I mean, about what happened. Because it's possible I..."


translate English day4_my_544f5980:


    my "No way! I stand by not wanting to leave an injured person behind... "


translate English day4_my_553ce965:


    my "I... I don't think you did anything wrong..."


translate English day4_my_bac3e806:


    my "But also... it's not like I don't disagree with what Cue said..."


translate English day4_my_81337d9a:


    pl "You mean...?"


translate English day4_my_a7881395:


    nar "She pauses for a moment, as if searching for the right words, before answering softly."


translate English day4_my_aec86995:


    my "That people who get caught up in the vestis don't live long..."


translate English day4_my_eb1e660c:


    pl "..."


translate English day4_my_2b0f3be7:


    my "Which is why... well... It's why I really want all of us to get along... Plus, I don't think Cue meant anything bad when he said that to us..."


translate English day4_my_f35ecea2:


    pl "*sigh*... You really are very sweet, Maya..."


translate English day4_my_4e7c9f33:


    my "N-No... You got it all wrong...!"


translate English day4_my_f74c01e1:


    pl "Alright. If that's what you think, then I'll try a little harder, regardless of how he reacts."


translate English day4_my_e0d52418:


    nar "My words seem to calm her down, the frown that's been on her face since I arrived softening out."


translate English day4_my_a95288af:


    pl "That being said, he should feel lucky that you care about him that much."


translate English day4_my_c4ff704d:


    my "There's something mysterious about him that makes it so I can never look away..."


translate English day4_my_c317dd29:


    pl "Mysterious?"


translate English day4_my_50830e8b:


    my "He...He has this aura of carrying experience far beyond his years, despite being not that much older than me. And I don't know where he's from or any of his friends..."


translate English day4_my_90ade135:


    my "It's just like my sister said, you don't find guys like him very often... He might be a boy, and yet his wrists are just as slender as mine..."


translate English day4_my_23cfc901:


    pl "Probably because he works all the time and never eats."


translate English day4_my_b9d0fa0d:


    my "Maybe. Which is why I worry sometimes about his health..."


translate English day4_my_0035da64:


    pl "You know, I worry about you, too, Maya."


translate English day4_my_dcfb65dc:


    my "You do...?"


translate English day4_my_3f480437:


    pl "You don't eat properly most days and you're already so small to begin with."


translate English day4_my_e22d56aa:


    pl "And with all the work you're doing, you're going to end up collapsing. I'm honestly more concerned about you than him."


translate English day4_my_458a6293:


    my "Ah, I h-have my reasons..."


translate English day4_my_d3fac757:


    pl "Oh, yeah? So explain to me why you need to skip meals."


translate English day4_my_e8a952d4:


    my "I d-don't want to get fat..."


translate English day4_my_6b65513f:


    pl "Seriously? You're almost excessively slim! Why would you even worry about something like that?"


translate English day4_my_250d2b77:


    my "Mmm..."


translate English day4_my_f7d9c99f:


    pl "That definitely wasn't a compliment. Besides, you're the one who said I could stand to gain a few pounds."


translate English day4_my_c1bb70fe:


    my "That might be what you think, [na2], but other people..."


translate English day4_my_e353a381:


    pl "That's absolutely false. First of all, it's strange that you can't eat right because you're worried about what others might think."


translate English day4_my_3334fc23_2:


    my "..."


translate English day4_my_a619a2a2:


    nar "Crap. I know Maya's sensitive about the word \"strange.\""


translate English day4_my_d496cea6:


    pl "I'm sorry, but I really do worry about you, Maya. Is there someone so special in your life that you need to go to these extremes for them?"


translate English day4_my_2dc04c52:


    my "Huh? I d-don't... I m-mean..."


translate English day4_my_e646c162:


    nar "Flustered, she quickly looks away, unable to hide the noticeable blush creeping over her cheeks."


translate English day4_my_baed76de:


    my "Can we j-just drop it please?"


translate English day4_my_a78c1db8:


    pl "If that's what you want, then I won't talk about it anymore. Just... be careful, okay?"


translate English day4_my_73e364c5:


    my "Sure..."


translate English day4_my_929dc5bd:


    nar "Let's change the topic."


translate English day4_my_91f12d22:


    pl "I'd kind of like to know more. You know, about what you like."


translate English day4_my_0c17ea92:


    my "I meant it when I said I love all living things. Even animals..."


translate English day4_my_266a5086:


    pl "So like cows and chickens?"


translate English day4_my_618d3902:


    my "Yeah. Those, too."


translate English day4_my_39c49702:


    pl "And bugs?"


translate English day4_my_cb39c396:


    my "I like them as well..."


translate English day4_my_0639e39b:


    pl "Frogs?"


translate English day4_my_564a34e4:


    my "They're pretty cute..."


translate English day4_my_0cbaed42:


    pl "I totally agree!"


translate English day4_my_dd210eeb:


    my "[na2], when you stare at me like that..."


translate English day4_my_722ad4d0:


    pl "I can't help it! Whenever you start talking about things you like, you get ten times as cute!"


translate English day4_my_0db32e08:


    my "I don't think I'm really that cute... Claire is far more adorable than I'll ever be..."


translate English day4_my_e0ac37b2:


    pl "You two must be close for you to immediately bring her name up when the word \"cute\" is mentioned."


translate English day4_my_159dfdca:


    my "Well, you see..."


translate English day4_my_628926b6:


    nar "Maya snips off one of the buds. She's been eyeing the shriveled up flower for a while now, probably conflicted over whether to cut it or not."


translate English day4_my_797b7c75:


    my "I'm just lucky that Claire likes me... for now, at least. "


translate English day4_my_d6c95027:


    my "When she finds out the type of person I really am, she'll probably leave me."


translate English day4_my_43db6950:


    pl "You're really a good person, though."


translate English day4_my_bac61268:


    my "You think so? ...Thanks. It makes me happy to hear you say that."


translate English day4_my_8878ab24:


    pl "I mean it."


translate English day4_my_e50a5740:


    my "...What do you like, [na2]?"


translate English day4_my_7631af35:


    pl "Huh?"


translate English day4_my_b0f9505f:


    my "We've just been talking about me this whole time, so... So I'd like to know what you like."


translate English day4_my_23da57ef:


    pl "Well, huh... Good question..."


translate English day4_my_0cb05856:


    nar "Basically, nothing. I've never held more than a passing interest in anything, "


translate English day4_my_d154556a:


    nar "since most things can easily be resolved without any serious investment on my part."


translate English day4_my_7b131c3c:


    nar "Come to think of it, Maya's been the only thing on my mind recently..."


translate English day4_my_40c6c811:


    my "[na2]?"


translate English day4_my_e573c340:


    pl "I like chatting with my friends in my free time. Like now!"


translate English day4_my_96c77367:


    my "You like... to chat?"


translate English day4_my_a7623218:


    pl "Or procrastinating and not showing up for work. I can see that disagreeable look on *his* face right now."


translate English day4_my_3dc92269:


    my "That seems like a pretty good thing to like..."


translate English day4_my_0d9c74f5:


    my "I like talking with my friends, too."


translate English day4_my_0a23226f:


    pl "Heh heh heh! Good then."


translate English day4_my_ddf952ef:


    nar "All of Maya's mannerisms are so subdued and minute that it's difficult to see sometimes, leaving me feeling vaguely uneasy."


translate English day4_my_4435b989:


    nar "It's why I can't leave her alone. I'm afraid she really would vanish into nothing the moment I did."


translate English day4_cr_f5481140:



    nvl clear
    br "\n Claire and I have fairly similar interests, but that didn't extend to our preferences. Our choice of food, for example.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_cr_2277afbd:


    extend "\nI can't stand salty or spicy things, so I don't season any of my food very much. As for Claire, though... As far as I can tell, she loves both sweet and greasy foods.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_cr_4ebf5b5d:


    extend "\nShe'll eat whole chunks of cheese and butter, for example, without a care in the world.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_cr_0390a1f0:


    extend "\nWe can still be together, though, which I think is because of the consideration we show each other.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_cr_cf27d904:


    extend "\nEven if her preferences are a little different than mine, it's not hurting me at all, so I figured it wasn't worth talking about."


translate English day4_cr_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day4_cr_ed83db1b:


    nar "I pass through the noisy central lobby of the temple and enter the hallway leading to the rear gates. There I see the dark emergency staircase."


translate English day4_cr_2dac9b10:


    nar "Enclosed by thick walls on all sides, it's quiet inside, almost like none of the hustle and bustle is actually happening around me."


translate English day4_cr_77b00b3e:


    nar "Although the place is completely covered in dust, the air soothes my soul, even granting me a strange sense of relief."


translate English day4_cr_9e1b4237:


    cr "Why, hello there!"


translate English day4_cr_7ca425de:


    nar "Or at least, it would have, had the high-pitched, cheerful voice unsuited to this peaceful, quiet space had not interrupted things."


translate English day4_cr_adee8b2f:


    pl "Whoa, Claire?! Don't jump out at me like that! You'll scare me!"


translate English day4_cr_4ffcf2c6:


    cr "I didn't jump out of anywhere! I've been here since before you were. Ah, since when you were going down the corridor..."


translate English day4_cr_b6f8004c:


    pl "Wait, you were in the corridor?"


translate English day4_cr_b8c46c46:


    cr "Yes. I happened to see you there,"


translate English day4_cr_30809f02:


    cr "but you didn't seem to notice me, so I secretly followed you!"


translate English day4_cr_1444810c:


    pl "But why bother sneaking around? You could have just said hello!"


translate English day4_cr_37932b53:


    cr "Well, I just did, remember?"


translate English day4_cr_78b16340:


    pl "Urk... That's some shady stalking, you know!"


translate English day4_cr_aea209fb:


    cr "I think the blame belongs on those who allow such stalking and sneaking to happen."


translate English day4_cr_b4fa379c:


    cr "From now on, I'd like you to pay more attention. Assassins could be small like me, creeping and crawling around in the shadows."


translate English day4_cr_4aef122e:


    cr "It was fortunate it was only me, but if it had truly been a killer, then...!"


translate English day4_cr_410b9f71:


    pl "Nobody would bother coming after my life. I'm just a priest."


translate English day4_cr_6ce36954:


    cr "The world is home to indiscriminate murderers who don't need reason or rhyme to kill, you know. Ah, how terrifying!"


translate English day4_cr_a2c653a7:


    pl "Then what does this terrifying little girl want with me?"


translate English day4_cr_c10e6c8d:


    cr "Oh... Hmm... Nothing in particular, really. I just wanted to say hello. "


translate English day4_cr_0a438a40:


    cr "Are you free?"


translate English day4_cr_e8e44de8:


    pl "As you can see, I'm free as a bird. More importantly, do *YOU* have time?"


translate English day4_cr_ea12c524:


    cr "But of course! If I didn't have free time, I wouldn't be chasing around a priest who definitely looked like he most certainly did!"


translate English day4_cr_d51f9a41:


    pl "Hey, not necessary!"


translate English day4_cr_b845cc4c:


    nar "It seems like she wants to keep talking here. "


translate English day4_cr_d25dd354:


    nar "But there's black dust stuck everywhere in this stairwell, including on the banisters. "


translate English day4_cr_3eaa96d5:


    nar "Without a choice, I take out a cloth, fold it a couple times, then set it on a stair of appropriate size."


translate English day4_cr_72e1284d:


    pl "Have a seat. That skirt must be expensive, yeah?"


translate English day4_cr_33f06e24:


    cr "Oh! How chivalrous, despite your appearance..."


translate English day4_cr_c78c0b2d:


    pl "Again, not necessary!!!" with sshake


translate English day4_cr_dcac9a97:


    cr "I will happily accept your show of goodwill, good priest!"


translate English day4_cr_b5726cfe:


    nar "Claire picks up her skirt hem and takes a seat quietly and modestly. I take my own seat a slight distance away."


translate English day4_cr_5e0ab0f3:


    nar "A dim, dusty emergency staircase and a flowery young girl is not a juxtaposition even villainous movie directors would think of."


translate English day4_cr_507d4ebd:


    cr "Do you always carry a handkerchief?"


translate English day4_cr_49b00080:


    pl "Not exactly, but today I happened to have it on me..."


translate English day4_cr_0b8918aa:


    nar "Seen from up close, Claire is almost like a doll. She smooths out the wrinkles in her skirt with her petite hands."


translate English day4_cr_17e31244:


    nar "Her nails are like gemstones, and her light blue hair still seems to have a luster even in this dark place."


translate English day4_cr_ff6d9cec:


    nar "Dolls don't talk, though. And as if to prove it, her small mouth, done up in light pink, immediately starts saying all sorts of things."


translate English day4_cr_fa576db8:


    cr "I see! Then you must have prepared it this morning specifically to have a seat on these dusty stairs!"


translate English day4_cr_922aab34:


    cr "Still, to think you would do so just to sit here alone in an emergency stairwell nobody knows about... You're surprisingly delicate, should I say, or perhaps simply dour..."


translate English day4_cr_e0be4e78:


    pl "Of course, my alone time has been ruined by a certain chattermouth!"


translate English day4_cr_cfb66def:


    cr "Ehehe. Then it's a good thing I came along right when you had some free time!"


translate English day4_cr_0566e044:


    pl "Right, right. Thanks a lot. "


translate English day4_cr_d1e39987:


    pl "Also, that's not a handkerchief--it's a scarf. It was in my luggage, but I don't really use it anymore."


translate English day4_cr_379e98aa:


    cr "Oh, so it's a personal item of clothing! I see. It's certainly red enough, isn't it?"


translate English day4_cr_f9f5a7f5:


    pl "The color is what convinced you?"


translate English day4_cr_49eac76e:


    cr "Red and black... Blood wouldn't stand out on it. Perfect for an assassin."


translate English day4_cr_91d86955:


    pl "We're still talking about that?"


translate English day4_cr_02f3acde:


    cr "Well, in terms of colors, I prefer blue. Oh, and pink, I suppose."


translate English day4_cr_4b829c68:


    pl "Your skirt is blue, too!"


translate English day4_cr_35d2671b:


    cr "Indeed it is. The abundance of frills is in style in the capital, as well!"


translate English day4_cr_1aacb2a1:


    pl "Makes no sense to me. If that's true, than all of my belts are definitely in fashion as well."


translate English day4_cr_dab1b599:


    cr "I don't know much about belts, but customized habits certainly do appear to be all the rage. Especially in this temple and especially in the Cleanup Department."


translate English day4_cr_0a05c1a9:


    pl "The regular ones don't fit me!"


translate English day4_cr_acc4da63:


    cr "I suppose it must be difficult being so short for a man!"


translate English day4_cr_1ded5f87:


    pl "Oh c'mon, I'm not THAT short! There's plenty of people shorter than me here." with sshake


translate English day4_cr_cdf94768:


    cr "But there are also plenty of people taller than you here. For example, the Magic Department's..."


translate English day4_cr_d476ee7a:


    pl "Lady Claire, here's something you may not know. Men keep on growing until age 25."


translate English day4_cr_b73f0686:


    cr "I never knew that... What scholar is your source?"


translate English day4_cr_94c67968:


    pl "Me!"


translate English day4_cr_0bee1804:


    cr "I thought as much."


translate English day4_cr_b4dc7100:


    pl "And being a little shorter than others comes with its own benefits."


translate English day4_cr_0fa18c2f:


    cr "That's a positive way of looking at it! What kind of benefits?"


translate English day4_cr_f80df30d:


    pl "I can sneak up behind tall people without them noticing. Like that person in the Magic Department..."


translate English day4_cr_29d382ea:


    cr "I believe you are still a bit too tall to do something like that, though."


translate English day4_cr_32adafa6:


    pl "Oh, just forget it!!!" with sshake


translate English day4_cr_2fe77fa8:


    nar "Claire smiles playfully--she must be enjoying this conversation."


translate English day4_cr_e7b999e7:


    nar "We're not even talking about anything, and yet with her, I can't help but feel like I'm coming to my senses a little."


translate English day4_cr_d6f0abec:


    nar "With how heavy the air in this quiet space is, Claire's high voice sounds louder than usual. "


translate English day4_cr_ac28be38:


    nar "The walls also create reverb, and I can feel the slight buzzing vibrations in my ears whenever she speaks."


translate English day4_cr_f8105072:


    nar "It's interesting--it kind of feels like we're cut off from the rest of the world."


translate English day4_cr_e42f1c98:


    pl "Come to think of it... I heard you're collecting temple rumors or something."


translate English day4_cr_731891e0:


    cr "Are you asking if I collect rumors?"


translate English day4_cr_5705102f:


    pl "Yeah. So, do you?"


translate English day4_cr_ac1e900d:


    cr "...Well, I do. I, Clione Myosotis, am a walking font of information here at the temple."


translate English day4_cr_838a9eed:


    pl "So why do you look so sad about it?"


translate English day4_cr_02cb673a:


    cr "It's just... When someone asks you something like that so boldly, doesn't it make you want to deny it outright? But no matter how I think about it, there's really no way to deny it, so..."


translate English day4_cr_8ccc817c:


    pl "Meaning you don't lie..."


translate English day4_cr_fc4f9297:


    cr "For me, the temple is like a nation unto itself. It truly has everything! "


translate English day4_cr_b45af828:


    cr "All the priests have food, clothes, and a roof over their heads here at the temple. I don't want to let even a scrap of information escape me!"


translate English day4_cr_d6e4507e:


    pl "The temple would be a much nicer place if more people had positive outlooks like you do."


translate English day4_cr_7457e9b3:


    cr "Oh, I think the current atmosphere is quite nice. After all, incidents and accidents are occurring every single day."


translate English day4_cr_6607c5fe:


    pl "Geez, I really hope not every day here has an accident or incident!"


translate English day4_cr_1c261f0e:


    cr "Ehehehe."


translate English day4_cr_05047473:


    pl "Anyway, if you got any fun rumors, let me hear 'em!"


translate English day4_cr_bb5bb971:


    cr "Hmm... I have this nugget of knowledge for you. It's said that 80%% of rumors created by a group of people are false."


translate English day4_cr_ab1bf999:


    pl "I never knew that. What scholar is your source?"


translate English day4_cr_39978e60:


    cr "Why, it's me!"


translate English day4_cr_2e559807:


    pl "I thought as much! Then how do you tell which rumors are true and which aren't?"


translate English day4_cr_3704e86f:


    cr "Well, I can't say it's perfect, certainly... But false rumors usually have one thing"


translate English day4_cr_2577f5a6:


    cr "in them that real ones don't: malice."


translate English day4_cr_87912f28:


    pl "Malice..."


translate English day4_cr_0eda5874:


    cr "People at the temple all love spicy gossip of all kinds. Complicated relationships, complex and contrived incidents..."


translate English day4_cr_941e2429:


    cr "Anything that tells them about someone's weaknesses. Carelessly telling someone rumors like those will only damage that person's reputation, nothing more and certainly nothing less."


translate English day4_cr_9120a840:


    pl "Yeah, you're right."


translate English day4_cr_65f69bce:


    cr "I'm quick to hear, but slow to speak! That's how I do things, anyway."


translate English day4_cr_fa3f59ec:


    nar "I've seen several times already how quick the temple priests are to pick up on rumors. Lies about a specific person--"


translate English day4_cr_75483ec0:


    nar "that's probably what all those rumors the empty-headed Cleanup Department priests have been tirelessly spreading about me. Even just this morning..."


translate English day4_cr_9f63b7f7:


    pl "You've probably heard a bunch of stuff about me then, huh?"


translate English day4_cr_9faab918:


    cr "Well, I certainly have... You are an object of interest right now, Lord [na]."


translate English day4_cr_b6122723:


    pl "Yeah, these last few days have really shown me how popular I am. Though I guess I can't be too happy about it... "


translate English day4_cr_035b4c1d:


    pl "These rumors you say you've heard about me--they're about the Magic Department, right?"


translate English day4_cr_c17535a5:


    cr "That particular information is closer to fact than rumors, if I'm being honest!"


translate English day4_cr_53146b93:


    pl "And you have more than that, don't you?"


translate English day4_cr_130f45bc:


    cr "Hmm..."


translate English day4_cr_dd57586b:


    pl "Like about their auxiliary bishop..."


translate English day4_cr_5c1e3ae7:


    cr "Oh... Wait, am I being interrogated right now?"


translate English day4_cr_212f3195:


    pl "No, I just wanted to know what kind of rumors were floating around. I want an honest answer!"


translate English day4_cr_cb7854eb:


    cr "Oh, but, but... It's not really rumors. It's more like fact... Huh?"


translate English day4_cr_3fbf8660:


    pl "So I really was the only one in the dark the whole time..."


translate English day4_cr_3ebc463a:


    cr "Rumors travel faster than the wind here, so please don't get so depressed. As people cut from the same cloth, let's do our best!"


translate English day4_cr_6fa6fe8d:


    pl "Sigh..."


translate English day4_cr_6fca4f68:


    pl "...Wait, we're definitely speaking the same language here, right?"


translate English day4_cr_a81e2416:


    cr "Yes, I do believe we are. Why?"


translate English day4_cr_f6d6f6a7:


    pl "Then what do you mean by \"cut from the same cloth?\""


translate English day4_cr_2483c8d3:


    cr "Hm... Why don't you read my mind again to find out?"


translate English day4_cr_94a1a3a4:


    pl "No can do. I'm out of juice."


translate English day4_cr_dae0df85:


    cr "Then it's a secret!"


translate English day4_cr_6a954a6c:


    pl "Aww..."


translate English day4_cr_2fca6e21:


    cr "Ehehe! Rumors do travel faster than wind here, so when the time comes, you'll find out."


translate English day4_cr_c6210b78:


    pl "And who am I going to find out from?"


translate English day4_cr_79129a2c:


    cr "From me, of course."


translate English day4_cr_ade6c728:


    pl "Well then, why can't you just tell me now?!"


translate English day4_cr_83645260:


    cr "I could, but you looked so confident that it made me want to bully you."


translate English day4_cr_5bbbf526:


    pl "Urk... I can't help my confidence, you know."


translate English day4_cr_f0dcb3c0:


    cr "Rumors... Hmm. Come to think of it, real rumors also have something that fake ones don't--evidence."


translate English day4_cr_cbbd3408:


    cr "Naturally, I wouldn't mind sharing a little of that sort with you. I understand better than anyone what feels like to be bursting with curiosity!"


translate English day4_cr_cba14e82:


    pl "Well, thanks. What kind of evidence?"


translate English day4_cr_cfa41f95:


    cr "Hmm. Such as, for example, the auxiliary bishop of the Health Department being terrible at cooking anything aside from sweets, I suppose."


translate English day4_cr_1bcf8cf7:


    pl "The Health Department... Oh, you mean Dr. Grette?"


translate English day4_cr_85682861:


    cr "Yes. Her food comes out tasting strange, as though she mixes up the spices and the order of the recipe."


translate English day4_cr_0d84fcc5:


    cr "I'm a personal witness to it, so this one can't be doubted!"


translate English day4_cr_0e33010d:


    pl "But if you found out for yourself, that's not even a rumor anymore. Still... That's interesting. I bet her sweets are best in the continent, too..."


translate English day4_cr_67584273:


    cr "I feel the same way! Still, I didn't leave any leftovers. It was my first food in three days, which means everything is delicious!"


translate English day4_cr_4f0ed1a3:


    nar "First food in three days...?"


translate English day4_cr_0fcbcc9c:


    pl "What, are you on some kind of crazy fad diet?"


translate English day4_cr_b7ec2160:


    cr "What? Oh, no, it's a personal matter. You see, I'm already light as a feather. "


translate English day4_cr_9375dfc3:


    cr "It's just that my reach only extends to certain things."


translate English day4_cr_71af1ad6:


    pl "Ha, if you keep going without food like that, you're bound to turn into an actual feather and float away!"


translate English day4_cr_2e1eb93f:


    cr "If that truly would let me fly, then I'd certainly like to try!"


translate English day4_cr_59b2c22e:


    pl "What else you got?"


translate English day4_cr_103f137c:


    cr "Hmm. Let's see... I know that the two new employees in the Health Department are siblings."


translate English day4_cr_12fdbf8c:


    pl "I'm sensing a trend here."


translate English day4_cr_263b7ad5:


    cr "Oh, right. I actually do most of my work helping the Health Department. I am a priest in training, after all."


translate English day4_cr_aa32dc0f:


    pl "Huh, so you're not just carrying around supplies."


translate English day4_cr_82930c76:


    cr "I only have to do that once a month! I'd like to see much more of the temple! "


translate English day4_cr_d6648384:


    cr "That's why I come to help out, usually three times a week."


translate English day4_cr_0ae08065:


    pl "Three times a week?"


translate English day4_cr_52abe5b3:


    cr "That's right! I wasn't supposed to come in today, but I ended up heading here anyway..."


translate English day4_cr_1e0797c7:


    pl "Coming to work on your day off? You must really like this temple, huh, Claire?"


translate English day4_cr_d45b071e:


    cr "...Are you doing this on purpose?"


translate English day4_cr_a46e1cbb:


    pl "Doing what?"


translate English day4_cr_8f34375e:


    cr "Ugh! I came all the way here to visit you, Lord [na]! You're a buffoon who knows nothing of a woman's heart!"


translate English day4_cr_0686adc7:


    pl "Wow. Lady Myosotis came here just for me? Wow, what a genuine honor!~"


translate English day4_cr_0b879b4d:


    cr "That... That's all?! Shouldn't your reaction be more like... \"Whoa...! She's so cute, and she came here to see me...!\""


translate English day4_cr_044c56d2:


    cr "and then your heart starts pounding?!"


translate English day4_cr_05487d86:


    pl "I feel like you maybe watch too many movies."


translate English day4_cr_e7190b20:


    cr "Well! Hmph, I don't know what I expected from you!"


translate English day4_cr_0270429e:


    nar "There were plenty of kids younger than me back home, but most of them were just barely toddlers."


translate English day4_cr_f64239f5:


    nar "If I could have stood the place for longer, I might have been able to watch over them as they grew up,"


translate English day4_cr_6f3fab7e:


    nar "but then I wouldn't have met Claire--and she is really cute."


translate English day4_cr_be0ebc26:


    cr "I feel this may be slightly early, but I must get going soon. It's very close to my commute time..."


translate English day4_cr_27f84dd8:


    cr "In any case, Lord [na], love one another as God loves you."


translate English day4_cr_6ce3b741:


    pl "This soon? Well, take care."


translate English day4_cr_1a7ee8bb:


    cr "...Come to think of it, why DO we say \"love one another as God loves you\" as a standard goodbye here at the temple?"


translate English day4_cr_8b543365:


    pl "Hmm... I figured it was in a holy book or something. It seemed like something only priests would say to each other, anyway."


translate English day4_cr_d3b58425:


    cr "Oh! Despite my not being a priest, nobody ever told me about that, so I never knew!"


translate English day4_cr_2b81223d:


    cr "Everyone else did it all the time, so I simply decided to imitate them! Geez!"


translate English day4_cr_0ef3b2ab:


    nar "And that right there seems like the adaptability that allows her to survive at the temple..."


translate English day4_cr_6bd7edb3:


    pl "You should come visit again tomorrow, Claire!"


translate English day4_cr_a480a733:


    cr "Oh, well... I'll need to give it thought, considering how you reacted just moments ago."


translate English day4_cr_326c5e75:


    pl "But why?! Come on, don't be like that."


translate English day4_cr_80bd989b:


    cr "I was shocked, you know! So shocked it felt like someone had boxed me right in the ear!"


translate English day4_cr_0e60950a:


    pl "Wouldn't it normally be more like someone hit you in the back of the head...?"


translate English day4_cr_cfa84f65:


    cr "No, no, no! When you're hit near the ears, you hear a ringing in your head and your vision starts to spin. Didn't you know that?"


translate English day4_cr_02582d02:


    pl "I mean, no? Why would I?"


translate English day4_cr_007e328e:


    cr "Then you simply lack life experience!"


translate English day4_cr_eb1e660c:


    pl "......"


translate English day4_cr_f0391b15:


    nar "Claire laughs in her usual cheery voice, but it sounds somehow ominous this time."


translate English day4_cr_1cdd8b64:


    nar "At the same time, though, I figure it's just my imagination. "


translate English day4_cr_153fb8f6:


    nar "Like this dark, enclosed space is making me worry too much."


translate English day4_cr_b2a3f432:


    nar "But if it wasn't just my imagination, then it was the fact that even she probably hasn't realized her own secret."


translate English day4_cr_5769eecd:


    nar "It's still quiet around us, without any birds out the window. And right next to me is Claire, seeming anxious at how the conversation suddenly faded."


translate English day4_cr_e72953c3:


    pl "Seriously, though. Won't you come again tomorrow? I want to talk to you more."


translate English day4_cr_b76dbe7a:


    cr "W-Well, if you insist... I shall consider it. I can give no guarantees, however..."


translate English day4_cr_67e3218e:


    pl "I'm happy you're just considering it. Really."


translate English day4_cr_85a70f24:


    cr "I'm... quite honored too, really..."


translate English day4_cr_0ab4a7aa:


    nar "She spoke the last bit in such a soft voice that it didn't create an echo for once. I give her a firm nod."


translate English day4_hk_T_620d843f:


    br "\n I've been thinking more about humanity and the nature of life itself ever since I started working as a priest in the Cleanup Department. Probably thanks to one lady in particular.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_hk_T_80e51492:


    extend " The bishop, who weeps over the death of strangers, who seems to sincerely care about the priests in her department... {w}{nw}"


translate English day4_hk_T_87d2d722:


    extend " and who gives their all to God in the name of devout belief. She's the one who offers words of comfort to the bereaved as well as the one who signs the documents needed for funeral rites.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_hk_T_33c78709:


    extend " I've repeatedly asked her about questions regarding life, though I should probably be asking her about death. It bothers me every time I see her.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_hk_T_2b333e26:


    extend "\nYet she always seemed happy to answer any question."


translate English day4_hk_T_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day4_hk_T_7f804a31:


    nar "It's the priest from the Academics Department who gave off those weird vibes. I think her name is Lavien Rose. "


translate English day4_hk_T_7faa87a2:


    nar "I got some good information from her. "


translate English day4_hk_T_0a072f83:


    nar "It might not have meant much to her, but it's an important clue in answering a question I've been harboring for a while now. "


translate English day4_hk_T_30a57f23:


    nar "First, it seems like pestis can alter a person's nature and psyche. Second, I'm not the only one who gets weird vibes from her."


translate English day4_hk_T_6fa02c62:


    nar "My heart begins to race as my footsteps quicken, though I stop right outside the workplace."


translate English day4_hk_T_43991393:


    nar "Securett's here. Apparently on his way back, his look of surprise is quickly replaced by a scowl, his eyes boring eyes into me."


translate English day4_hk_T_7cab32a3:


    nar "Great. I wasn't expecting to run into this jerk again today."


translate English day4_hk_T_1c5afa37:


    sc "Heading to the workplace?"


translate English day4_hk_T_b799a671:


    nar "It's not like him to initiate conversation, though there's a lack of warmth that's usually included in a greeting or inquiry into one's health. "


translate English day4_hk_T_c3dc6f26:


    nar "My mood takes a turn for the worse hearing the caution in his voice, despite having done nothing to deserve it."


translate English day4_hk_T_348f87ba:


    pl "That's honestly none of your damn business."


translate English day4_hk_T_80fff029:


    sc "Oh, but it is. You have a tendency to interrupt the bishop during the breaks that she so rarely gets."


translate English day4_hk_T_d9e89e28:


    pl "The bishop gets to take breaks? I've honestly never noticed..."


translate English day4_hk_T_77791284:


    sc "..."


translate English day4_hk_T_45db1007:


    pl "You probably don't realize this since you never pay attention to anyone other than yourself, but the bishop enjoys talking with me."


translate English day4_hk_T_f39d8431:


    sc "Tch. If you knew anything, you wouldn't engage in conversation with her."


translate English day4_hk_T_e1643392:


    pl "Huh? What the hell are you talking about?"


translate English day4_hk_T_b86339e2:


    sc "There are more important things for you to do than flirt with women. "


translate English day4_hk_T_cb66f261:


    sc "You need to work on your immaturity or rather, learn from the mistakes you've made today so you don't repeat them."


translate English day4_hk_T_fac170ef:


    pl "...Still trying to convince me everything that happened was my fault?"


translate English day4_hk_T_7073f69c:


    sc "The Cleanup Department's always been understaffed... in fact, it still is."


translate English day4_hk_T_a8bb4e00:


    sc "And yet here I am, during one of the busiest times of the year, cleaning up after your inexperienced ass, unable to do my own job properly."


translate English day4_hk_T_3675e571:


    sc "Do you know what that means?"


translate English day4_hk_T_c01a73cd:


    nar "None of this has anything to do with me. "


translate English day4_hk_T_d7266fc8:


    nar "The blame for my inability to do what needs to get done coupled with trainees repeatedly making the same mistakes lies squarely on the shoulders of our SENIOR who didn't give us enough guidance."


translate English day4_hk_T_8c2ce6a2:


    nar "If he's as busy as he claims to be, then why doesn't he just lock himself up somewhere and get it all done?"


translate English day4_hk_T_0093bf13:


    nar "I want to ask him why he came all the way out here just to get himself involved, but I decide to ignore his comment instead."


translate English day4_hk_T_014f13be:


    pl "Is the bishop in the workplace right now?"


translate English day4_hk_T_299f13fe:


    nar "Securett grows quiet for a moment, as if irritated by my attitude. He doesn't look like he's at a loss for words."


translate English day4_hk_T_f11f9ef7:


    nar "When he looks up again, his cold gaze is staring straight at me, glaring angrily, his shoulders trembling faintly."


translate English day4_hk_T_fd75b213:


    sc "You need to learn when to keep your mouth shut and to keep in mind where you stand."


translate English day4_hk_T_d64363bd:


    sc "If you're looking for someone to pass the time with, go somewhere else. Haku is not the type of woman you should approach out of idle curiosity or a passing interest."


translate English day4_hk_T_469ece3e:


    nar "His clear enunciation gives him a firm tone of voice. His cold manner of speaking, as if spitting out dirt, has a degree of heat mixed in."


translate English day4_hk_T_42826ae1:


    nar "He's probably been sitting on this for a while."


translate English day4_hk_T_b2f9dfb0:


    nar "Granted, I never approached the bishop because I was attracted to her, as a straight man might to a charming lady. "


translate English day4_hk_T_0de201d2:


    nar "Though going after someone in the quest of knowledge, or more accurately speaking, simple curiosity isn't the wisest decision I ever made. "


translate English day4_hk_T_2470eca7:


    nar "Still, there's no way I'm agreeing with him."


translate English day4_hk_T_f011d90f:


    pl "What makes you so sure that's what I'm doing?"


translate English day4_hk_T_4a66f9ef:


    sc "...You're nothing more than a human, with all the flaws that entails."


translate English day4_hk_T_42c2999b:


    nar "What in the world did I do to him to make him think so low of me? "


translate English day4_hk_T_b451c46e:


    nar "Clearly, I must've touched a nerve at some point to elicit such scathing insults. And he's been this way all afternoon."


translate English day4_hk_T_21267f9a:


    nar "I clench my fists tightly as I feel myself about to explode, but I take a deep breathe and am able to calm myself down. "


translate English day4_hk_T_5d5f3a9c:


    nar "I would never hit someone smaller and weaker than me. "


translate English day4_hk_T_acf79fb4:


    nar "And above all else, I'd never lose my temper in the middle of a conversation."


translate English day4_hk_T_1c02aaeb:


    nar "After speaking his mind, Securett shuts his mouth once more, "


translate English day4_hk_T_e32e9e7f:


    nar "leaving us to stare at each other silently."


translate English day4_hk_T_bf94112a:


    nar "The sharp clack of her heels shatters the chilled, tense air between us. The sound alone is enough to herald her arrival."


translate English day4_hk_T_646fc6f4:


    nar "She turns her head as she passes us by, seemingly oblivious to the overwhelming tense atmosphere."


translate English day4_hk_T_f0affc64:


    hk "Are you two having a pleasant conversation?"


translate English day4_hk_T_77791284_1:


    sc "..."


translate English day4_hk_T_8f4c74cf:


    nar "Securett glances over his shoulder at Haku once before walking away without a single word of greeting. "


translate English day4_hk_T_144cf5f8:


    nar "The elegent ring of her voice seems at odds with the sterile clack of her high heels."


translate English day4_hk_T_eb9f2216:


    nar "She watches Securett walk off with a dubious look on her face. I can sympathize."


translate English day4_hk_T_35104be4:


    pl "That guy's such a...!"


translate English day4_hk_T_a9a7103e:


    hk "You mean Brother Rafe? He is a very competent priest."


translate English day4_hk_T_a2602ac1:


    nar "Securett Rafe... So that's his last name, huh? I've been working alongside him for four days now, but this is the first time I heard his full name. "


translate English day4_hk_T_af27ef9c:


    nar "The guy doesn't talk at all, and everytime I see him, he's always in a foul mood. "


translate English day4_hk_T_1d496224:


    nar "I assumed he had to have a last name, but I never would've thought I'd hear it from Haku instead of Securett himself or another priest. "


translate English day4_hk_T_c8b06d06:


    nar "Truly bizarre, considering his attitude towards her."


translate English day4_hk_T_4cb3a219:


    pl "Were you two together?"


translate English day4_hk_T_a062409a:


    hk "I was making sure the jobs from this morning were being taken care of, "


translate English day4_hk_T_18039ec6:


    hk "though Securett tends to help take care of all that."


translate English day4_hk_T_dd1ddc6b:


    pl "He helps you out?"


translate English day4_hk_T_416a3799:


    hk "Indeed. Securett's a really nice young man. Very kind and incredibly meticulous."


translate English day4_hk_T_cc4969b8:


    nar "I almost burst out laughing. Nice? Kind? Meticulous? None of those words sound like that pompous prick."


translate English day4_hk_T_d0383d31:


    hk "His only fault, if I had to pick one, would be his lack of friends... "


translate English day4_hk_T_77d87095:


    hk "So I'd appreciate if you'd try to get along with him as much as possible."


translate English day4_hk_T_c8ed05e0:


    pl "Look, bishop, I'm sorry to interrupt such a heartwarming story, but I'm sure there's a good reason why that grouch doesn't have any friends."


translate English day4_hk_T_ffed6fc9:


    hk "But poor Securett works so tirelessly and without complaint, even when I ask him to take care of paperwork and business affairs."


translate English day4_hk_T_77080e20:


    hk "He also always brings me meals and takes care of me when I forget things. I'm kind of scatterbrained."


translate English day4_hk_T_9a3696c7:


    pl "That guy...?"


translate English day4_hk_T_3063e1b2:


    hk "Don't call him that! Friends refer to each other by name, right? "


translate English day4_hk_T_7a0d51f7:


    hk "He's also incredibly good with his hands. He always helps tie my hair up for me. Hehehe..."


translate English day4_hk_T_3811b024:


    nar "Despite his clear distaste for her, Securett really goes above and beyond keeping up appearances of acting as her assistant."


translate English day4_hk_T_123f5178:


    nar "The more I learn about him, the weirder he is. Hearing the bishop gush so positively about him only fires up my competitive spirit."


translate English day4_hk_T_033ae066:


    nar "Maybe he'll stop complaining all the time if he hears how much she loves talking with me straight from her own mouth."


translate English day4_hk_T_1e34868a:


    pl "You know, I'm pretty good at braids, too. Feel free to ask me for help instead of him the next time you need a hand."


translate English day4_hk_T_e6c0ee2a:


    hk "Oooh! I can't wait "


translate English day4_hk_T_02a5e3a3:


    nar "Through the veil of her half-transparent sleeves, I notice her gloves are misty with water. Looking closer, I realize the edges of her sleeves are damp as well."


translate English day4_hk_T_ec4fae42:


    nar "Did she wash her hands with her gloves on? Realizing I'm staring at her, she hides both of her hands in her long sleeves."


translate English day4_hk_T_494fca25:


    hk "It's p-pretty noticeable, huh? I splashed some holy water on them. To purify my soul..."


translate English day4_hk_T_e3cec457:


    pl "Holy water, huh? I've heard of it. The stuff that wards off demons and washes away sin?"


translate English day4_hk_T_aa869417:


    hk "One and the same! You seem to know a lot about it."


translate English day4_hk_T_90fdb641:


    pl "Haha! I've been reading through some of the books in the library."


translate English day4_hk_T_1c5484c0:


    hk "Holy water is used to help wash away impurities. It contains refined salt..."


translate English day4_hk_T_2e1e3d36:


    pl "Yech! Why salt, of all things?"


translate English day4_hk_T_310864ed:


    hk "It's soluble without dissolving completely."


translate English day4_hk_T_27b3eb43:


    hk "Salt is the only rock that's both edible and doesn't rot and one of the only nutrients necessary for sustaining human life."


translate English day4_hk_T_392e1e92:


    hk "The vow of an everlasting covenant."


translate English day4_hk_T_02b6b98c:


    pl "Wow... So Securett drenched himself in holy water earlier today? You must've needed a lot of salt for that."


translate English day4_hk_T_0d613d33:


    hk "Heheh... That wasn't holy water. I figured he'd be happier with baptismal water "


translate English day4_hk_T_49f8333e:


    nar "She goes to cover her laughter with her sleeve, though immediately pulls it away upon noticing the dampness. I laugh on her behalf."


translate English day4_hk_T_e6737df4:


    nar "There's still aspects to her that I find unpleasant, and to be honest, I'm not sure how dependable she is, and yet I still prefer her company."


translate English day4_hk_T_4626106b:


    nar "I'm slowly getting used to the acrid smoke, which doesn't seem as strong today."


translate English day4_hk_T_2d2f5d52:


    nar "This sense of security has more to do with her role as bishop than any personal inclination I might have toward her. "


translate English day4_hk_T_a4c8e28d:


    nar "I feel more comfortable dealing with the bishop, who's able to take charge when need be, "


translate English day4_hk_T_6f8c608b:


    nar "than the other priests who change their personalities based on perceived interests or commonalities."


translate English day4_hk_T_519357e0:


    nar "She suddenly turns to look at me, as if curious if I'm scratching my nose or something. Her pure white hair is even more dazzling up close."


translate English day4_hk_T_39f51b83:


    nar "Her eyes, nose, and mouth are merely body parts designed to help her breathe, and yet the way they look on her face makes her seem almost impossibly beautiful."


translate English day4_hk_T_a8bfe569:


    hk "That faint smell of perfume... You really were in the library, weren't you?"


translate English day4_hk_T_121f4266:


    pl "Oh... Yes. I guess I still retain the smell of that place, hrm? Whatever aromatic they use is quite strong."


translate English day4_hk_T_fc9d1181:


    pl "You know what I'm talking about? It's almost like perfume."


translate English day4_hk_T_90fa82c5:


    hk "It's just a basic deoderant. A floral fragrance... Though the stronger the smell it's mixed with, the worse it gets..."


translate English day4_hk_T_13756370:


    pl "That's true... So you don't wear perfume at all?"


translate English day4_hk_T_66509c21:


    hk "I do. Whenever the need to impress arises."


translate English day4_hk_T_f1817f4b:


    pl "I see..."


translate English day4_hk_T_27d3c805:


    hk "With that said, do you think they're alright? The priests from the Cleanup Department..."


translate English day4_hk_T_dc7dcbc3:


    pl "They're fine. Oh, though I apologize for going into the library without clearing it with you first. "


translate English day4_hk_T_9fad814d:


    pl "I did chat with Evelynn a bit, and it seems like she thinks quite highly of me."


translate English day4_hk_T_94fd55d8:


    pl "Thanks to her, I've been reading through a mountain of books that'll help make my job here easier."


translate English day4_hk_T_6e1a6c26:


    hk "Evelynn..."


translate English day4_hk_T_26ece4f2:


    nar "Her expression darkens slightly. That I usually only ever see her sporting her trademark easygoing smile makes her grim expression seem even darker."


translate English day4_hk_T_3ec15404:


    nar "Clearly there's something going on between them, and I decide to go ahead and pry for information."


translate English day4_hk_T_5116f525:


    pl "Did something happen between you two?"


translate English day4_hk_T_158d1918:


    hk "Huh? No... Not exactly..."


translate English day4_hk_T_d9f6c184:


    pl "It's fine, I promise I won't tell anyone."


translate English day4_hk_T_25a7ca8f:


    hk "Well... It's just... She's an incredibly difficult person to deal with."


translate English day4_hk_T_f7bb5811:


    pl "Difficult? Like, personality-wise?"


translate English day4_hk_T_902d5916:


    hk "Not quite... When my father was still a bishop in the Academic Department, Evelynn had just gotten baptized and was acting as his assistant."


translate English day4_hk_T_e740cf85:


    hk "Being so young, I heard stories of how she looked after me, though I don't remember any of it."


translate English day4_hk_T_90ad6ea9:


    hk "She's very intelligent, kind,"


translate English day4_hk_T_e517a394:


    hk "and someone I regard with a great deal of respect, but..."


translate English day4_hk_T_feed897b:


    hk "I just always get so anxious around her."


translate English day4_hk_T_1cd4d49e:


    nar "Maybe it means that with her, even Bishop Haku is like a toad under a snake's glare."


translate English day4_hk_T_edf60342:


    nar "I didn't realize she had this unexpected flaw,"


translate English day4_hk_T_033d42ad:


    nar "but knowing Evelynn's overwhelmingly chilling personality, it's not hard to understand why."


translate English day4_hk_T_7b10d5d2:


    nar "What interests me the most is her own past."


translate English day4_hk_T_6a9a9885:


    pl "You've been here in the temple since you were young?"


translate English day4_hk_T_30fdda2f:


    hk "Or so I've been told... however... Mm... only in the library located in the Academics Department. "


translate English day4_hk_T_69b251e5:


    hk "I guess as a child, I really loved to read books."


translate English day4_hk_T_b675ec19:


    pl "Interesting. I'd love to hear more. If you keep telling me about your childhood, maybe it'll eventually spark some kind of memory."


translate English day4_hk_T_a860f689:


    hk "I really don't remember anything from when I was a young girl... It's all just a bunch of vague, fluffy hazy images..."


translate English day4_hk_T_8aba8eec:


    hk "My memories don't really begin until after I left the temple and began living on my own, with a little help from the Health Department's bishop."


translate English day4_hk_T_0584f2c8:


    pl "Wow! That's an unexpected duo. Why did you decide to start living on your own?"


translate English day4_hk_T_d7e1967c:


    hk "Well..."


translate English day4_hk_T_9e7ef6bd:


    nar "She closes her eyes, as if conjuring up images of her past, while repeatedly rolling her head in slow circles. "


translate English day4_hk_T_e1ee8539:


    nar "Having seen her done this before, it must be a habit for when she's deep in thought."


translate English day4_hk_T_2f59a999:


    hk "Ugh... I really don't remember..."


translate English day4_hk_T_88c13f40:


    pl "I wonder why your memories are all shattered like that."


translate English day4_hk_T_430f412d:


    hk "As I've mentioned several times by now, I don't remember anything from my childhood... Though my father talks about it from time to time."


translate English day4_hk_T_52614e83:


    pl "Weird... So the memories you do have might not even be correct?"


translate English day4_hk_T_1acacde4:


    hk "No. My father wouldn't lie to me. He always guides me toward the truth, with his voice and his hands."


translate English day4_hk_T_b11b7650:


    hk "Which is why I adore him as deeply as I do."


translate English day4_hk_T_0346cb80:


    pl "I feel like \"adore\" is maybe not the right word in this situation... Though who cares. You didn't ask my opinion anyway."


translate English day4_hk_T_f7b22f3b:


    hk "Heheheh! My heart is the very epitome of sacrity."


translate English day4_hk_T_68aa3cda:


    nar "It sounds less like a sacred heart and more like a lascivious one."


translate English day4_hk_T_a285eb30:


    pl "It sounds like you've been helped by a great number of people here, from the Academics bishop to the Health Department."


translate English day4_hk_T_4acc139c:


    pl "She still looks out for you, even now."


translate English day4_hk_T_12891021:


    hk "Yes, and I feel truly blessed. God has graced me with a number of amazing relationships, "


translate English day4_hk_T_129f6bba:


    hk "and these interpersonal relationships inevitably give rise to new life. "


translate English day4_hk_T_f23e7854:


    hk "I was born from a similar fateful connection."


translate English day4_hk_T_6eadb4d7:


    nar "I feel like I've heard this same story somewhere before."


translate English day4_hk_T_71e3a550:


    pl "You can thank God, but you should also thank the folks who watched over you."


translate English day4_hk_T_749b9559:


    hk "Of course. Being thankful to the good graces of God means not forgetting the grace shown to one by others. "


translate English day4_hk_T_21ecf30c:


    hk "I'm grateful for all the relationships I've built that made me who I am today. "


translate English day4_hk_T_abeb56d9:


    hk "I am also grateful beyond what words can say that you took the time to pay me a visit today, Brother [na]."


translate English day4_hk_T_7fd8929a:


    nar "It almost makes me sound like a bonus surprise to one of God's miracles. Though hearing her sincere gratitude isn't that bad."


translate English day4_hk_T_3d61c752:


    nar "Compared to most other people, Haku can be a difficult person to converse with. But unlike her seemingly disingenuous facade, it's clear that she's always in deep meditation."


translate English day4_hk_T_1d12b194:


    nar "She sees each priest as individuals. It worries me a little, but it's kind of charming, too."


translate English day4_hk_T_bbe4e680:


    nar "Anyone who hasn't spent enough time with the bishop inevitably misunderstands her. I was the same way at first, and I'm sure that jerkass is no different."


translate English day4_hk_T_7c2439ee:


    nar "I have no idea how long he's been working by her side, but it's clear that Securett doesn't see her the way she truly is."


translate English day4_hk_T_f2100bc0:


    nar "Which is why he says the things he does."


translate English day4_hk_T_25b4e15d:


    pl "So you were here in the workplace throughout your entire lunch break?"


translate English day4_hk_T_5251e312:


    hk "Actually... I spent some time with Maya in the garden."


translate English day4_hk_T_a602aaf4:


    pl "The garden? You mean the rose arbor? Maya really likes spending time there."


translate English day4_hk_T_6760272a:


    hk "It used to be part of the Cleanup Department. I used to be the primary caretaker... "


translate English day4_hk_T_6a2e5400:


    hk "though it brings me joy to know another priest has taken an interest in its upkeep."


translate English day4_hk_T_257816b1:


    pl "The rose garden did strike me as something you'd have a hand in."


translate English day4_hk_T_c33a513c:


    hk "You really think so?"


translate English day4_hk_T_f698d371:


    pl "Huh? Well, yeah..."


translate English day4_hk_T_ddab2d78:


    hk "You mean because both me and the roses are equally as thorny?"


translate English day4_hk_T_043bab8c:


    pl "No, because you're both gorgeous! Why so negative?"


translate English day4_hk_T_486dcffa:


    hk "If I wasn't so busy all the time, I could have taken better care of them... In fact, I really haven't had much time to stop by the gardens lately..."


translate English day4_hk_T_b47240e4:


    hk "Are the roses all mopey and extra thorny without me?"


translate English day4_hk_T_8c87aaab:


    pl "I'm sure they understand, considering you raised them so well."


translate English day4_hk_T_c7c0567b:


    hk "Fantastic... I'm glad to hear that"


translate English day4_hk_T_16b16be0:


    nar "I feel like I'm comforting a small child."


translate English day4_hk_T_eb1e2039:


    pl "What did you talk about with Maya?"


translate English day4_hk_T_1bed6205:


    hk "Ah, how to take care of the garden and about the roses. Though... she wasn't very talkative."


translate English day4_hk_T_246f1634:


    pl "She's pretty quiet and not very talkative by nature."


translate English day4_hk_T_cf6911ca:


    hk "She's so cute. I wish I could get to know her better..."


translate English day4_hk_T_d3732cb0:


    pl "You think she's adorable, too, huh?"


translate English day4_hk_T_b93cda19:


    hk "Of course, though her uniform isn't quite correct..."


translate English day4_hk_T_bd223fae:


    pl "Her uniform isn't correct?"


translate English day4_hk_T_eb81f468:


    hk "And neither is yours, [na]. You're so sparkly all over, like some kind of tough guy "


translate English day4_hk_T_5f4d1b05:


    pl "Ugh... I figured if I didn't mention it, you'd give me a pass."


translate English day4_hk_T_857b1854:


    hk "Clothing inspections are a necessary evil, though I'm not that strict about it. "


translate English day4_hk_T_82845919:


    hk "Everyone yearns to wear cute, fluttery dresses and sparkling, cool clothes, right?"


translate English day4_hk_T_a41ff1dc:


    pl "Which is why the priests in the Cleanup Department wear whatever they want?"


translate English day4_hk_T_71f92f56:


    hk "Seeing cute girls makes me happy "


translate English day4_hk_T_e51737fb:


    pl "I think your clothes are pretty cool, or at least really impressive."


translate English day4_hk_T_c274efc1:


    hk "This outfit is a compromise of sorts... After all, as you can tell, I'm far from cute..."


translate English day4_hk_T_4c8b1249:


    pl "Huh? What does that have to do with anything?"


translate English day4_hk_T_045bead5:


    hk "F-F-For example, there's no way I'd ever be able to pull off a skirt as frilly as Maya's. " with sshake


translate English day4_hk_T_bb456246:


    hk "I can't believe you made me explain that to you...!"


translate English day4_hk_T_a5f0ac13:


    pl "That's not... What I mean is, you're more than cute enough..."


translate English day4_hk_T_867edf7b:


    hk "I like girls who are slender with just the right amount of pudge. It's just my personal preference!"


translate English day4_hk_T_deb47cae:


    pl "I g-get it! I know what you're trying to say! No need to say more!"


translate English day4_hk_T_f85285c2:


    nar "If being small and a little pudgy is the bishop's requirement for cuteness, then she's on the opposite of the spectrum."


translate English day4_hk_T_a7972bd1:


    nar "Despite the fact that she's always smiling and fairly subdued, the slant in her eyes gives her the shifty appearance of a fox."


translate English day4_hk_T_2ccacb85:


    nar "She's also got long slender fingers mostly hidden by her overflowing sleeves, and she's taller than I am."


translate English day4_hk_T_4f7cdf57:


    nar "Though honestly, I think she's fine the way she is."


translate English day4_hk_T_7c6d6474:


    pl "I didn't realize you had such lofty ideals. At any rate, I think you're already gorgeous."


translate English day4_hk_T_49dfce3a:


    hk "*sigh*... This happened a long time ago, but I remember my sudden growth spurt while in the Academics Department. I thought I'd never stop growing... "


translate English day4_hk_T_9d6d1ef0:


    hk "Even recently, it seems like I've grown a little taller... Ugh. I restricted my diet and everything."


translate English day4_hk_T_c299be11:


    pl "You deprive yourself of food?"


translate English day4_hk_T_14bc65de:


    hk "I used to from time to time as a student. But then one day, I ate a huge amount of rice all by myself, and to make matters worse, I don't remember doing so at all... "


translate English day4_hk_T_331b781c:


    hk "So I stopped restricting after that."


translate English day4_hk_T_9ab3a7e4:


    pl "That's good to hear but also slightly terrifying..."


translate English day4_hk_T_c471fdfd:


    hk "Heheh! Hunger is one of the most primitive pains humans can feel."


translate English day4_hk_T_a7d7fb98:


    hk "None of the priests here have to worry about that, of course."


translate English day4_hk_T_268294b5:


    hk "But even the flowers in the garden need water and sunlight to survive."


translate English day4_hk_T_560b3d38:


    pl "People who care about flowers and animals enough to care for them are truly amazing. Their sense of responsibility is impressive."


translate English day4_hk_T_89c068f7:


    hk "\"Life\" and \"responsibility\" are two sides to the same coin. I think about it often."


translate English day4_hk_T_f1809aa1:


    pl "It sounds like a much bigger deal when you refer to it as a life."


translate English day4_hk_T_a6c6e1b6:


    hk "It is, in fact, an extraordinary deal. It's easy to lose a life, which is why it's so important to listen carefully. "


translate English day4_hk_T_d6034c20:


    hk "You mustn't look away. You never know when it might vanish."


translate English day4_hk_T_a37ef79b:


    pl "If I remember correctly, the elders in my hometown always said one's lifespan was predetermined at one's birth. "


translate English day4_hk_T_1e7a6575:


    pl "Which is why it was so important to live a virtuous life."


translate English day4_hk_T_b5a953cc:


    hk "Heheh... They're right... I've come across an abundance of different lives through my line of work. "


translate English day4_hk_T_68e6fdb3:


    hk "And I've had more brushes with death than most. "


translate English day4_hk_T_ec3c21e7:


    hk "Our job is mostly about washing away the sins of the dead while also guiding lost souls that remain trapped in their bodies... "


translate English day4_hk_T_96a6658a:


    hk "but that's not all. We also must dispose of those poor souls that've been sucked into the pestis."


translate English day4_hk_T_2fd85442:


    nar "The memory of the priest from earlier in the day flashes before my eyes."


translate English day4_hk_T_2c9af0eb:


    nar "A living corpse with his limbs twisted at impossible angles, blind to the world in front of him, his lungs crushed yet pleading desperately for help through melting lips."


translate English day4_hk_T_eff290e4:


    nar "Haku was there before I realized what was going on. A soul consumed by pestis... even now, those words swirl through my head."


translate English day4_hk_T_bda3b773:


    hk "I often find myself facing those bound for execution."


translate English day4_hk_T_59869948:


    hk "A person who is about to die has no soul. The soul dies before the body does."


translate English day4_hk_T_97c36dbd:


    hk "Ah, do you know what I mean by the death of a soul?"


translate English day4_hk_T_7c39ef6e:


    pl "You mean that they've given up on life?"


translate English day4_hk_T_a4373a4f:


    hk "Very close. Life is something that's sacred... eternal, pure, and unchanging."


translate English day4_hk_T_66c03d0d:


    hk "God breathes life into every creature that blooms on earth, flies through the sky, and crawls under the ground. Or to be more precise, he creates the vessel that houses their soul."


translate English day4_hk_T_2cc66055:


    pl "So you're saying that our life doesn't end with the destruction of our corporeal bodies. That we are in fact, repeatedly born again through the transference of our souls."


translate English day4_hk_T_274df813:


    hk "I believe it's similar to what you refer to as reincarnation."


translate English day4_hk_T_b908ecb1:


    pl "Right, yeah. So what's different?"


translate English day4_hk_T_ec2acc8a:


    hk "It's not that they're necessarily different. The reason some people can be resurrected is because our souls are immortal. "


translate English day4_hk_T_206dc8ad:


    hk "Dream, be ambituous, think, and feel. As long as you have a unique personality and an id, brother, your soul will never die."


translate English day4_hk_T_7365af13:


    pl "Then why do people die at all?"


translate English day4_hk_T_fbe8cacd:


    hk "It happens when we've completed our predetermined destinies. Life is the heavenly decree to live and let live."


translate English day4_hk_T_4d7ee883:


    hk "When God grants life to a human being, it's not about survival alone."


translate English day4_hk_T_340ea7ce:


    hk "The meaning of life is strengthened by sharing cultures and forming bonds... This is referred to as destiny or karma."


translate English day4_hk_T_a6c813d0:


    pl "So in other words, someone dies once they've done everything they could? "


translate English day4_hk_T_eb6a71c2:


    pl "But I know many people who've died regretting their inability to do anything at all... "


translate English day4_hk_T_7717f571:


    pl "Does it mean their role in life was to be consumed by pestis?"


translate English day4_hk_T_ed1f95d0:


    hk "Yes. All of them were simply following God's will."


translate English day4_hk_T_98f88a63:


    hk "But when a soul dies before the body does, when they openly defy their own destiny..."


translate English day4_hk_T_629fbed3:


    hk "that's when God sends down pestis, to collect those wayward souls and bring them back to heaven."


translate English day4_hk_T_e83464ec:


    pl "Can you tell when your soul dies?"


translate English day4_hk_T_f0b0c3b1:


    hk "I don't think so. Can you feel if your own soul is dead, Brother [na]?"


translate English day4_hk_T_26e69b10:


    pl "Well, I don't think it's dead, but also I'm not sure if it's alive, either."


translate English day4_hk_T_8d84e452:


    hk "Your soul lives, Brother. Thank you for talking with me. I can tell you enjoy it"


translate English day4_hk_T_3eb9444a:


    hk "and that it makes you think and ask questions, just like that one--which means your soul lives."


translate English day4_hk_T_ba69eb40:


    hk "We play a part in each other's lives, do we not?"


translate English day4_hk_T_5cc69126:


    nar "Despite not having said anything weird, I realize I'm incredibly nervous. "


translate English day4_hk_T_bc7be3a5:


    nar "The more I think about it, the more weirded out I get. It must be her voice."


translate English day4_hk_T_78ffd6d3:


    nar "Her voice is so low and even-toned that it sounds almost masculine, her facial features fairly androgynous. "


translate English day4_hk_T_9d8787cc:


    nar "It seems silly to me that she always pitches her voice purposefully higher. Add in her slow method of speech and it makes everything harder to understand without intense concentration."


translate English day4_hk_T_111580d0:


    nar "But maybe that's part of her charm. I don't really get it, but when said with that pecular tone of voice, I'd believe anything she told me."


translate English day4_hk_T_bc76cf70:


    nar "There's an odd credibility to it, so much so that if she told me flowers bloom from baked beans, I'd believe it."


translate English day4_hk_T_7ba96234:


    hk "You mentioned something about a strong sense of responsibility, Brother [na]. Why?"


translate English day4_hk_T_049471c3:


    pl "I definitely don't have enough of that. Whether for plants or animals... "


translate English day4_hk_T_aa10b9af:


    pl "taking care of a life means accepting responsibility for it."


translate English day4_hk_T_32884862:


    hk "Responsibility is something that inevitably accompanies all of our encounters, does it not?"


translate English day4_hk_T_3c39349c:


    pl "You're responsible for a great number of things, huh?"


translate English day4_hk_T_a6ceabd7:


    hk "Me? Well, yes, I do carry that burden. Fairly seriously as well..."


translate English day4_hk_T_e3d326a3:


    nar "She nods to herself as she appears to count something on her fingers. She spreads all five fingers wide apart."


translate English day4_hk_T_14a77d25:


    hk "But I can only do as much as is possible. I'm always bearing the weight of my responsibilities..."


translate English day4_hk_T_cde84b89:


    pl "That's part of your job?"


translate English day4_hk_T_d2e7065e:


    hk "Yes, but it's also something I've been tasked with as part of my role in life. A task given to me by our father who art in heaven."


translate English day4_hk_T_a2707244:


    hk "You know, [na], I am all too happy to shoulder the burden of your responsibilities as well. You are one of my priests, after all..."


translate English day4_hk_T_aa6d9c1c:


    pl "Haha! While I'm grateful, I can't let someone else do my job for me..."


translate English day4_hk_T_08fb84e1:


    hk "I can't do the work for you, but I can share your karma. "


translate English day4_hk_T_f5e53d1d:


    hk "If you feel your responsibility, your sin is too heavy, "


translate English day4_hk_T_61ecc922:


    hk "I can share the weight with you and make it easier to carry."


translate English day4_hk_T_31470914:


    nar "I still don't fully understand what that word means. "


translate English day4_hk_T_843aef2b:


    nar "Since I can remember, the adults around me have pressed the importance of accepting responsibility for things, and I've lived my life bearing the burden of doing so."


translate English day4_hk_T_2294807b:


    nar "Perhaps it's a comforting reminder to rely on myself?"


translate English day4_hk_T_9f73e1de:


    nar "Or is it more like a threat to not lose sight of my karmic role?"


translate English day4_hk_T_27fe503b:


    nar "Maybe it's just a meaningless phrase."


translate English day4_hk_T_fcd68c5f:


    nar "But I just nod, my body seemingly moving on its own before I've fully grasped the meaning of the word. "


translate English day4_hk_T_d9fe192d:


    nar "It's the effects of her voice again. Seeing the look of amusement on her face, all I can think about is the textbook definition."


translate English day4_hk_T_3ad03526:


    hk "I'm truly sorry, but I have to get going."


translate English day4_hk_T_143be381:


    pl "Oh. Did I get in the way of your work?"


translate English day4_hk_T_9c1897d7:


    hk "No, no! Not at all. It's been so long since I've had such a nice conversation with someone, and I truly enjoyed it. I had so much fun talking so sooo much with you."


translate English day4_hk_T_755c473c:


    pl "Th-Then I'll be sure to come back tomorrow. Do you always work here during lunch?"


translate English day4_hk_T_ff487f55:


    hk "Oooh! I'd love it if you did! "


translate English day4_hk_T_3221f7c5:


    hk "The day is far from over yet, so please take care... and don't stay out too late."


translate English day4_hk_T_14ee88cc:


    pl "Yep, I'll see you tomorrow. And you take care as well..."


translate English day4_hk_T_ddddbe33:


    nar "I watch her walk away with slow, wavering steps, her movements as awkward as ever."


translate English day4_hk_T_3e1b0b72:


    nar "With her body wobbling worryingly from side to side, I find myself about to rise to my feet each time she looks about to fall."


translate English day4_hk_T_ff326d76:


    nar "She finally vanishes from view, and I suddenly start coughing. It's not like the air quality has suddenly gotten worse, but rather, that I find it hard to breathe."


translate English day4_hk_T_e6e2a222:


    nar "I try thumping my chest lightly with my fist, but once I become keenly aware of the odd sensation, it won't go away that easily."


translate English day4_gr_T_cb8602f0:


    br "\n She refers to herself as an old lady, but it's exactly that attitude that makes her so popular among the perceptive yet still childlike priests in the temple.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_gr_T_cd9ab7f8:


    extend " As far as I know, Haku never turns anyone away, even if she's in the middle of something, and never scolds anyone, no matter how selfish they might come off.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_gr_T_4d4095a5:


    extend " Even when she acts hurt over a prank, it doesn't seem serious or like she takes it to heart, which is probably why everyone likes her as much as they do.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_gr_T_e3f07328:


    extend " I was one of many who adored her smile, but watching her sometimes fills me with a rage that I can't understand."


translate English day4_gr_T_0391818e:



    nvl clear
    br "\n The folks in the Disposal Team have a tendency to openly express contempt, and I've heard her name mentioned within their vicious gossip circle at least several times.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_gr_T_519f7618:


    extend " Knowing her as well as I do by now, it's mostly ridiculous garbage, and yet, for some reason, I always find myself listening in."


translate English day4_gr_T_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day4_gr_T_a8b5794c:


    nar "She's the first person I think of when I need to talk to someone."


translate English day4_gr_T_60afcaa8:


    nar "The light in the infirmary, which is always on, spills out into the hallway, pushing back the ever-present temple shadows."


translate English day4_gr_T_275ed55b:


    nar "Who can look at this light and not feel a sense of relief?"


translate English day4_gr_T_16911392:


    gr "Welcome."


translate English day4_gr_T_17bd3aed:


    nar "She greets me cheerfully with her usual warm smile, almost as if she was expecting me. "


translate English day4_gr_T_5e276748:


    nar "Seeing that smile of hers always leaves me feeling vaguely uneasy for some reason."


translate English day4_gr_T_bbf459fc:


    nar "That anxiety then gradually spreads through my entire body, until it fills my mouth."


translate English day4_gr_T_aacf1b11:


    pl "Morning, doc! You looked pretty busy when I saw you in the hospital earlier, so I wasn't sure if you'd be here."


translate English day4_gr_T_309e726a:


    gr "Hehehe! I had a feeling that you might show up sometime today."


translate English day4_gr_T_cc423c0f:


    pl "Wow! You seem to know everything."


translate English day4_gr_T_528ebebb:


    gr "It was just a hunch! An intuition of sorts, if you will. I've always been told I have extraordinary luck when it comes to meeting people."


translate English day4_gr_T_18fc7edc:


    pl "Like how the first person I met upon arriving here was you!"


translate English day4_gr_T_f1fa0f58:


    gr "Hahaha! Is that so? Well, go on! Don't just stand there. Sit, sit!"


translate English day4_gr_T_3e4eb117:


    nar "I sink into the comfortable cushions on her couch and she brings out a plate of pastries for me."


translate English day4_gr_T_2f0ccfdd:


    nar "Today's snack plate is filled with bite-sized muffins. The tiny chocolate chips that are sprinkled here and there are slightly melted."


translate English day4_gr_T_955092de:


    pl "By the way, why do you always make them so small?"


translate English day4_gr_T_7ab65df6:


    gr "Hrm? You mean my pastries? It's so I can make enough to go around."


translate English day4_gr_T_0d00c41f:


    gr "Bigger treats take longer to make and faster to consume."


translate English day4_gr_T_e4392abe:


    pl "I see. I guess the secret is to make a lot and keep them small."


translate English day4_gr_T_b9019825:


    gr "It's better to have too much than not enough, even if you end up with extras."


translate English day4_gr_T_5916788f:


    pl "I'll take one!"


translate English day4_gr_T_2129bb8b:


    gr "Please do. You like milk, don't you, [na2]?"


translate English day4_gr_T_136844b7:


    pl "You remembered?!"


translate English day4_gr_T_575992f4:


    gr "Of course I did!"


translate English day4_gr_T_a8307492:


    nar "She casually fills a clear glass with milk. Her bite-size muffins are as delicious as always, though they're maybe a little too sweet for me."


translate English day4_gr_T_236c746c:


    nar "She must think that all youngsters like sweets."


translate English day4_gr_T_ce373c3d:


    gr "How's your friend? She seemed worn out the last time I saw her..."


translate English day4_gr_T_83a0d345:


    pl "Oh... Maya's fine. You just gave her a bit of a scare."


translate English day4_gr_T_5462676b:


    gr "I'm glad to hear... Girls her age tend to be very sensitive."


translate English day4_gr_T_eff8f833:


    pl "We had a bit of trouble at the library, but I hope she'll be able to spring back..."


translate English day4_gr_T_3a3b6885:


    gr "You went to the library?"


translate English day4_gr_T_1521813d:


    pl "Yep! I wanted to look something up. It was pretty creepy though."


translate English day4_gr_T_f923e4ae:


    gr "Heh, sounds like you guys had an interesting time."


translate English day4_gr_T_9069444c:


    pl "It's not funny. I almost got skewered by a bunch of priests from the Academics Department."


translate English day4_gr_T_f5f61643:


    gr "Oh, my..."


translate English day4_gr_T_f3a5add9:


    pl "I'm just glad their bishop showed up in the nick of time."


translate English day4_gr_T_e3af6d75:


    gr "Me, too!"


translate English day4_gr_T_b79ae299:


    pl "The bishop told me she made sure Maya made it back to the dorms safely, but who knows if it's true..."


translate English day4_gr_T_000d754d:


    gr "I'm sure there's no need to worry! Evelynn is as kind as she looks, and a favorite among the youngsters here in the temple."


translate English day4_gr_T_ec8a3fb6:


    pl "That's right! Doc... You and the bishop are pretty close, aren't you?"


translate English day4_gr_T_84949939:


    gr "Yep. She's one of my best friends, in fact. We go waaaaay back! She's honestly done so much for me."


translate English day4_gr_T_4e144a92:


    gr "She's really smart and a good listener to boot!"


translate English day4_gr_T_e0f1a09c:


    pl "Th-That's hard for me to imagine..."


translate English day4_gr_T_96aa7f92:


    gr "That's great that you two are going to the library to study, though!"


translate English day4_gr_T_dddce1d5:


    pl "I feel like \"great\" is pushing it... I just needed to look something up."


translate English day4_gr_T_a22ec189:


    gr "And why was that?"


translate English day4_gr_T_0655f94e:


    pl "Well... actually, it's kind of embarrassing, but it was about something Securett said to me while we were working earlier."


translate English day4_gr_T_14a7845a:


    gr "Hahaha! And what did Rett have to say?"


translate English day4_gr_T_bdb358c2:


    nar "He told Maya not to call him that, and yet the doctor uses the nickname without hesitation."


translate English day4_gr_T_faab1be9:


    pl "It's probably my fault for still not fully understanding the language and culture here in the capital, "


translate English day4_gr_T_e3fd61d5:


    pl "but basically he's always telling me that I'm a two-stig or that I'm a dumb hick and goes out of his way to constantly ignore me."


translate English day4_gr_T_ce575804:


    gr "That must make you feel pretty bad, huh?"


translate English day4_gr_T_ff37d35c:


    pl "I dunno about bad, but... it definitely gets on my nerves."


translate English day4_gr_T_f1acea72:


    gr "Heh! It's clear that he wants something from you."


translate English day4_gr_T_46da01b2:


    gr "He's desperate for any kind of attention. He'd never admit it, but that guy's pretty sensitive."


translate English day4_gr_T_2c339c53:


    gr "I'm sure his stinging remarks come from a place of caring for you."


translate English day4_gr_T_929d31d5:


    pl "Maybe..."


translate English day4_gr_T_4c90f0c9:


    gr "I'm pretty confident! His attention is always hyperfocused on those around him, to the detriment of himself at times."


translate English day4_gr_T_9d1df82e:


    gr "He's worked until he's passed out several times before."


translate English day4_gr_T_57e1a7c9:


    pl "I don't get it. Why's he so desperate...?"


translate English day4_gr_T_9ebb9587:


    gr "Maybe there's something he wants to protect in his own way."


translate English day4_gr_T_62cc821f:


    pl "Like what?"


translate English day4_gr_T_4d679d3e:


    gr "Good question. It differs depending on the person, right? "


translate English day4_gr_T_78f06298:


    gr "Sometimes it's another person or an object, but most of the time it's something more abstract, like a point of view or an emotion."


translate English day4_gr_T_f381a97a:


    gr "Like family, for example. Or a matter of pride. Stuff like that."


translate English day4_gr_T_0986af8f:


    pl "Hrm... It's hard for me to understand without a concrete example..."


translate English day4_gr_T_49d5a887:


    gr "You've never felt that way before, [na2]?"


translate English day4_gr_T_53e9acd4:


    pl "Well... Even if I was forced to say something, I can't think of anything. I don't think I've ever had something that important in my life."


translate English day4_gr_T_f1ec2474:


    gr "Even if it doesn't seem like a big deal to others, as long as it's important to you, then that's all that matters."


translate English day4_gr_T_67ccdb7c:


    gr "For me, I truly cherish the time we share together, just like this. I'd do anything to protect it."


translate English day4_gr_T_a7f760e2:


    pl "That does sound like something worth protecting!"


translate English day4_gr_T_f8e5ce5e:


    gr "Hehehe! I'm glad you feel that way, but you should think of something else that's important to you, too."


translate English day4_gr_T_f9977149:


    gr "Maybe it'll be the spark you need to do something truly spectacular,"


translate English day4_gr_T_8c8a8a14:


    gr "like your sudden enthusiasm toward studying in the library today."


translate English day4_gr_T_2f870cf2:


    pl "Okay, I'll give it some thought. With that said, I appreciate you helping me see things from that jerk's point of view, but still... "


translate English day4_gr_T_921eb07e:


    pl "He's pretty bad when it comes to interpersonal relationships."


translate English day4_gr_T_aa3721ab:


    gr "When you see someone struggle that hard, doesn't it make you want to cheer them on all the more?"


translate English day4_gr_T_3605b923:


    pl "I can see why you'd think that because you're looking at the situation from a third-party perspective. But when you're the recipient, it doesn't feel as great."


translate English day4_gr_T_2f8bce13:


    gr "That's true... From my vantage point, all I want is for everyone to get along."


translate English day4_gr_T_29be72e1:


    pl "Yeah, well I wish I could do that for you, but you can't always get what you want, as they say."


translate English day4_gr_T_b9ec8cbc:


    nar "If I'd been more confident in doing whatever I wanted, I wouldn't be in this mess now."


translate English day4_gr_T_1fbd8a14:


    nar "What bothers me most about this is it's more than a simple argument."


translate English day4_gr_T_3b8dd60d:


    nar "That three days have passed since I arrived and I still haven't gotten used to the job or the people here is making me start to doubt my own competence. But also..."


translate English day4_gr_T_a7798bd5:


    gr "[na2]."


translate English day4_gr_T_508c333b:


    pl "Hm?"


translate English day4_gr_T_eca1ad4b:


    nar "The thought crossed my mind for barely a moment, and yet it seems like she noticed the look of concern on my face. With her gaze locked on me, she suddenly stops talking."


translate English day4_gr_T_11316437:


    nar "I feel slightly uncomfortable having those clear green eyes of hers studying me so intently."


translate English day4_gr_T_b954f3e0:


    pl "Wh-What's wrong?"


translate English day4_gr_T_3c2de325:


    gr "You don't look well. Is there something else you wanted to talk to me about?"


translate English day4_gr_T_703f69ac:


    nar "Do I look sick? Since when? Worry and that feeling of anxiety from earlier begin crawling up my spine,"


translate English day4_gr_T_6212224e:


    nar "though they instantly dissipate as soon as I look back at Dr. Grette."


translate English day4_gr_T_ceef4521:


    nar "With just the two of us in here, the infirmary is quiet. Sitting there, wordlessly, all I can hear is a faint breeze and the ticking of the clock. There's no sign that anyone else will be stopping by any time soon."


translate English day4_gr_T_da9acb06:


    pl "I can't get anything past you, huh?"


translate English day4_gr_T_2dba8107:


    gr "You know you can always talk to me about whatever's bothering you."


translate English day4_gr_T_a2c2e1c6:


    pl "I'm just not sure what your reaction will be..."


translate English day4_gr_T_67447847:


    nar "Unlike the amicable atmosphere between us, my throat's getting progressively dry, making it hard to speak. My thoughts begin spinning chaotically as I try to get the recent events in order."


translate English day4_gr_T_fc6ec394:


    nar "I'd never planned on telling anyone about what happened the other night. It's not something I can bring myself to recount and not something I really want to relive."


translate English day4_gr_T_79ff483f:


    nar "What I really need her input or advice with is the thing that's been bothering me the most--the visions I've been plagued with lately, including this morning."


translate English day4_gr_T_1e7718d0:


    pl "...I'm not sure what your reaction will be, but... well... I've been having these hallucinations lately."


translate English day4_gr_T_935ed158:


    gr "What kind of hallucinations?"


translate English day4_gr_T_363dcf79:


    pl "It's almost like my memory cuts out, but only for a moment... and it's not like I pass out or anything."


translate English day4_gr_T_a3038675:


    pl "Other people have told me that I continue acting normally, like nothing's wrong."


translate English day4_gr_T_bc2be87d:


    gr "Hm, I see. But when you come to, you're somewhere else? Something like that?"


translate English day4_gr_T_0374518c:


    pl "It's not that bad, but more like... I can't remember anything that happens in that short span of time. Does that make sense?"


translate English day4_gr_T_05046853:


    gr "It certainly does. Do you experience anything else?"


translate English day4_gr_T_cd95d4f0:


    pl "Well... I also see weird things. Like corpses, body parts, and people's guts..."


translate English day4_gr_T_484d8d32:


    pl "I honestly thought I was just seeing things. It was pretty shocking the first time it happened."


translate English day4_gr_T_8f78f480:


    gr "I'm sure you've witnessed a lot of truly horrific scenes on the job. I get it."


translate English day4_gr_T_5041f2be:


    pl "Right? Lately, it seems like every day brings another dead body for me to deal with..."


translate English day4_gr_T_df1c99ff:


    gr "Anything else?"


translate English day4_gr_T_ba88acdd:


    pl "Well..."


translate English day4_gr_T_be118863:


    nar "I've been having these dreams about an angel."


translate English day4_gr_T_6cec1aaf:


    nar "I clamp my lips shut, trapping those words in my mouth before I can speak them."


translate English day4_gr_T_dfc99479:


    nar "The face of the angel that I saw last time. All I know for sure is that I know her, "


translate English day4_gr_T_60e42b3f:


    nar "and yet I still can't quite recall what it looks like, as if something's blocking me from the memories."


translate English day4_gr_T_df69fd32:


    nar "Perhaps she's someone from my daily life, who I already know. But that's as far as I'll allow my mind to go."


translate English day4_gr_T_61ba2b78:


    nar "Something that absurd is truly terrifying to think about."


translate English day4_gr_T_48804759:


    gr "Any other symptoms...?"


translate English day4_gr_T_5c2701ec:


    pl "...No, there's nothing else. Well, other than the sky always being so dark makes it hard to sleep."


translate English day4_gr_T_958fd8f9:


    gr "I actually feel the same way. Though it's not like the midnight sun has never come to the capital...{w} It just makes a lot of things inconvenient. I miss the moon."


translate English day4_gr_T_1cade035:


    pl "But the sun suits you better, doesn't it?"


translate English day4_gr_T_003bb79d:


    gr "Oh, you!{w} The sun suits you well too, [na2]! You seem like the energetic type, after all."


translate English day4_gr_T_474b67f3:


    pl "Well, of course. The sun's always hot and high in the sky where I come from~"


translate English day4_gr_T_5303d764:


    gr "Honestly, I sympathize completely. This isn't the first time the capital's had to deal with this constant polar night... but it does present some challenges. I miss the sun."


translate English day4_gr_T_89cd7363:


    pl "I'm sure you're even more beautiful bathed in sunlight!"


translate English day4_gr_T_003bb79d_1:


    gr "Oh, you!{w} The sun suits you well too, [na2]! You seem like the energetic type, after all."


translate English day4_gr_T_5b9221cb:


    pl "You're probably right. The sun was always shining back where I come from."


translate English day4_gr_T_ee045325:


    nar "I decide to keep my mouth shut. Besides, it's probably not a big deal. "


translate English day4_gr_T_1544a651:


    nar "It's not that unusual to have the same dream two days in a row. I'm sure it doesn't mean anything."


translate English day4_gr_T_a2922bca:


    pl "Are there a lot of folks dealing with similar issues?"


translate English day4_gr_T_3f3cd9b7:


    gr "There are many people here with a variety of problems, including memory issues."


translate English day4_gr_T_780bdf03:


    gr "With that said, the way you experience this kind of thing is not necessarily the same as everyone else."


translate English day4_gr_T_29ba1c84:


    gr "There's plenty of youngsters dealing with troubling hallucinations, which could be classified as daydreams or dj vu. It happens when faced with horrific situations."


translate English day4_gr_T_1e907fe4:


    pl "That's kind of terrifying... Is it something that can be fixed?"


translate English day4_gr_T_8560c52a:


    gr "Of course! Just about every condition that exists in this wide, wide world can be fixed."


translate English day4_gr_T_362600fd:


    gr "Many folks believe pestis is an act of god, but these kinds of mental afflictions are entirely thanks to an individual's psyche and mental health."


translate English day4_gr_T_d7d90911:


    gr "It's a sickness with a man-made cure."


translate English day4_gr_T_021f1523:


    pl "Wow... I didn't realize there were other people here with similar memory lapses..."


translate English day4_gr_T_53c33010:


    gr "There is still a great deal of dependance on God and pestis here in the capital. Not to say that I DON'T believe in God, mind you."


translate English day4_gr_T_942279eb:


    gr "Still, I think it's important to understand illnesses instead of blaming everything on pestis."


translate English day4_gr_T_597a22db:


    gr "I hope superstitions and old wives tales won't lead the young into a den of snakes or have them drinking the blood of beasts."


translate English day4_gr_T_acfc054b:


    pl "Honestly, everything would be a lot easier if people just listened to their doctors more..."


translate English day4_gr_T_2f1fe3ce:


    gr "It's admirable you think that way. But I didn't start out spouting such eccentric ideology, understand?"


translate English day4_gr_T_9fc30103:


    gr "I owe thanks to a special someone who taught me everything I know today while I was still just a student."


translate English day4_gr_T_35118cde:


    pl "Someone from your grade school days?"


translate English day4_gr_T_04e33383:


    gr "Yep, back when I was younger than you are now. "


translate English day4_gr_T_47964927:


    gr "He wasn't that much older than me, yet he was much wiser, able to meditate on things better than I ever could back then."


translate English day4_gr_T_4159df93:


    gr "To be fair, I was pretty stubborn at the time. "


translate English day4_gr_T_90f2322f:


    gr "We were practically inseperable as we studied various ways to help folks get better."


translate English day4_gr_T_d3fea255:


    gr "It's a little embarrassing to admit, but it's thanks to him that I'm able to talk to folks here, like what we're doing right now."


translate English day4_gr_T_0fce0890:


    pl "You seem pretty delighted to talk about him. You must have a lot of good memories of him."


translate English day4_gr_T_4c6c91e2:


    gr "I do, huh? Really? My, my... Well, fond memories are really all you got after you reach a certain age. "


translate English day4_gr_T_08498b85:


    gr "You're right, though. I have many great memories of the time we spent together. We spent decades together."


translate English day4_gr_T_0884ab65:


    nar "Ruffling her hair in embarrassment, I notice the light sparkling off her ring finger."


translate English day4_gr_T_baea1e97:


    nar "A silver ring. Noticing my gaze, she laughs innocently. She's smiling in my direction, and yet I can tell her eyes are looking right through me."


translate English day4_gr_T_e8ad63f6:


    gr "This silly thing? Yeah... We're still together, even now."


translate English day4_gr_T_bf27442d:


    gr "Hehehe... Don't tell anyone, 'kay?"


translate English day4_gr_T_a494c90e:


    nar "For the first time since we met, the expression on her face is not that of a kindly doctor listening to my woes, but that of a woman."


translate English day4_ar_T_e61f7371:


    br "\n Everyone at the temple--no, everyone in the capital--is probably interested in Arne Alternata.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_ar_T_902d8bc4:


    extend " Even for a new arrival in the capital like me, it only took a few days for me to understand her position.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_ar_T_db125ccf:


    extend " But what they know of her only relates to her being a mage--they don't know what she's like personally.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_ar_T_f124e756:


    extend " Essentially raised in a bubble, she began learning spells as soon as she started reading her letters.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_ar_T_8b46af6b:


    extend " Due to that, even as an adult, she doesn't partake of any food from outside her sphere, even on a whim.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_ar_T_c02a9cf0:


    extend " She doesn't play around, either--she wouldn't even know what that dirty ball covered in sewn-together cloth is for."


translate English day4_ar_T_4818ea21:



    nvl clear
    br "\n Could they ever imagine her--the eldest daughter of the Alternata family--sitting in front of a sandwich, not knowing what to do?{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_ar_T_3a6fbeb2:


    extend " And even if they did imagine that scenario, I'm probably the only one in the capital who knew that her answer would be{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_ar_T_fa7eec71:


    extend "\nthat she was waiting for a fork. The Arnie I know is exactly that kind of lady.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_ar_T_27d57420:


    extend "\nI doubt anyone could imagine it, nor would I expect she'd want anyone to know about it."


translate English day4_ar_T_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day4_ar_T_8138cd53:


    nar "As I awkwardly walk up to the training grounds, I spot a familiar face."


translate English day4_ar_T_1ca6c5ae:


    nar "Vivid hair color that doesn't match this place and a relaxed posture--it's Lavien Rose, who I just met at the library earlier."


translate English day4_ar_T_e34ebca6:


    pl "Oh..."


translate English day4_ar_T_c5ea07fe:


    rv "Oh! If it isn't little [na]. I didn't think I'd run into you here."


translate English day4_ar_T_3f958a84:


    pl "I could say the same. This is the room where the Magic Department trains... Did you need something from them?"


translate English day4_ar_T_71bd1a41:


    rv "Yes. To tell the truth, I, fortunately, have something of a connection to one of the auxiliary bishops here."


translate English day4_ar_T_3a40196b:


    pl "Auxiliary bishops... You mean Arnie?"


translate English day4_ar_T_226c69d1:


    rv "Oh, I do of course know Lady Arne, but I was here on a visit to her younger brother."


translate English day4_ar_T_3e1c6ebd:


    pl "Huh. You and Enoch know each other... That's a surprise."


translate English day4_ar_T_16b66f8e:


    rv "I hear that often. If one were to judge a person based on the first information one receives, "


translate English day4_ar_T_bef2d1cf:


    rv "then as a lowly person, I am not fit to stand at Lord Enoch's side."


translate English day4_ar_T_5a3c130c:


    pl "Nah, I more meant your personalities. I don't discriminate like that."


translate English day4_ar_T_6bc9a9e8:


    rv "Well, well... You have me there. Would you like to go in together?"


translate English day4_ar_T_668ae9d7:


    pl "Huh? But I--"


translate English day4_ar_T_80c4d44b:


    rv "You're here because you need something, just as I do, yes?"


translate English day4_ar_T_335c6c8d:


    pl "Well, yeah, I guess... Sure, let's go in."


translate English day4_ar_T_d18b662c:


    nar "Lavien opens the door, and naturally, I follow her inside."


translate English day4_ar_T_d6732b7b:


    nar "The Magic Department priests all stop their chaotic goings-about because of it, and one by one, they yield the way."


translate English day4_ar_T_46806a45:


    nar "Arnie, having spotted us, walks over, her expression a bit dubious."


translate English day4_ar_T_03df87cc:


    ar "Are you two here together today? I must say, it's a rather unusual combination."


translate English day4_ar_T_3d649d12:


    rv "We actually met just outside. Have you been well, Lady Arne?"


translate English day4_ar_T_e7581dec:


    ar "I've been quite well, thank you... I see you're looking well yourself, Sister Lavien."


translate English day4_ar_T_9d2b85bf:


    nar "As I wait behind Lavi, Arnie sneaks a smile over to me, then bows her head. I get embarrassed and nod back. I'm not used to stuff like this."


translate English day4_ar_T_fa25e92a:


    nar "It's making me self-conscious."


translate English day4_ar_T_0ce13e69:


    rv "May I ask after Lord Enoch's whereabouts?"


translate English day4_ar_T_de2e4a31:


    ar "Enoch? Oh, I'm terribly sorry. He left but moments ago."


translate English day4_ar_T_34a2a659:


    rv "I see... The icon of loyalty himself is away? That's unusual."


translate English day4_ar_T_fd3a3623:


    ar "He should return soon... But if you'd like, you can take a seat and wait for him."


translate English day4_ar_T_c5b55ace:


    rv "Oh, but I couldn't..."


translate English day4_ar_T_6b4c3ae8:


    nar "Lavi looks up and meets my gaze. Is she trying to figure out how I feel about this?"


translate English day4_ar_T_79248aed:


    pl "...What are you looking at me for?"


translate English day4_ar_T_88fd3de1:


    rv "Weren't you planning to speak with Lady Arne?"


translate English day4_ar_T_2bc4526f:


    pl "What?! No, I've got nothing to do with this! And I'm sure she's really busy anyway! Aren't you, Arnie?"


translate English day4_ar_T_45d00977:


    nar "Maybe that reaction came off as unnatural. Arnie's face clouds a little."


translate English day4_ar_T_df6e13dd:


    nar "She lowers her eyes and brings her fingers together before eventually looking at me again."


translate English day4_ar_T_24948c33:


    ar "In that case, I'm very sorry for the wait. Brother [na2], if it's alright with you, "


translate English day4_ar_T_d725b97a:


    ar "would you like to wait inside with Sister Lavien?"


translate English day4_ar_T_b6376752:


    pl "Huh? The two of us?"


translate English day4_ar_T_d077fecb:


    ar "Yes..."


translate English day4_ar_T_bd51205a:


    pl "I mean, sure..."


translate English day4_ar_T_69fe6e72:


    rv "I have no objections either."


translate English day4_ar_T_797e2b3b:


    nar "Arnie finally puts her hands down."


translate English day4_ar_T_b9bcc1aa:


    ar "Thank you for overlooking this rudeness. I'll be there right away. I'll only be a few moments."


translate English day4_ar_T_150a1f43:


    nar "I guess it can't just be the two of us today. Which isn't a big deal for me. Actually, I prefer it this way. "


translate English day4_ar_T_19deac25:


    nar "Being face to face with her would just be uncomfortable for me..."


translate English day4_ar_T_6a7c160d:


    nar "It's my second time in the hot-water room, and Lavi stands out against its immaculate cleanliness. To the others, though, I probably look every bit the outsider as she does."


translate English day4_ar_T_2539c186:


    rv "Are you certain about this, little [na]?"


translate English day4_ar_T_362337dc:


    pl "Nothing to be certain about. I was never against this to begin with."


translate English day4_ar_T_603f33f6:


    rv "I think that once in a while, if you have something to say, it would be good to let it out. "


translate English day4_ar_T_2e6add6b:


    rv "The chance to do so won't always be right beside you."


translate English day4_ar_T_f40855fb:


    pl "Despite how you look, you're pretty nosy..."


translate English day4_ar_T_7db8479f:


    rv "Have I displeased you?"


translate English day4_ar_T_84911194:


    pl "Nah, I was actually sort of thinking the same thing."


translate English day4_ar_T_1d252010:


    nar "She really picked up on that one."


translate English day4_ar_T_5d91e6f6:


    pl "But I'm serious. I wasn't trying to get out of being with you. Really."


translate English day4_ar_T_644effac:


    rv "Well, then. I'm honored to hear it."


translate English day4_ar_T_3b824e93:


    pl "It's true I was a little hesitant to have a face-to-face meeting with her, so..."


translate English day4_ar_T_f4f052ff:


    rv "Did something happen between you and her?"


translate English day4_ar_T_3192d542:


    pl "Nah, not really. Just me thinking too much, probably."


translate English day4_ar_T_64fb5c3a:


    rv "You're worried about something."


translate English day4_ar_T_4addb38a:


    pl "I guess so... Not worth telling anyone, if you ask me. And it would be rude to say it to you anyway."


translate English day4_ar_T_224422e2:


    rv "You're worried about something that has to do with her."


translate English day4_ar_T_c1029358:


    pl "But she's the last person I want to talk about it with. Just the fact that I'm worried about something would make it harder on her..."


translate English day4_ar_T_e226d5a5:


    rv "Such problems do spring up from time to time. "


translate English day4_ar_T_94724a6a:


    rv "But let me ask you this, little [na2]. Are these worries ones that you'll find an answer to just by worrying about it?"


translate English day4_ar_T_b5fe383c:


    pl "...No."


translate English day4_ar_T_407359fa:


    rv "And why is that?"


translate English day4_ar_T_27afeb9e:


    pl "Because it's not something I can do anything about. I don't have the right to decide, and neither does Arnie..."


translate English day4_ar_T_0cf865fa:


    nar "I've already made peace with it. Several times. I don't have any reason to hate her, or avoid her. It's all set in stone anyway."


translate English day4_ar_T_c9013213:


    nar "And yet I still feel uncomfortable coming face-to-face with her. It's probably not resentment or avoidance, but a much more personal issue."


translate English day4_ar_T_3ae4d54a:


    nar "I think I just lost my sense of what attitude to have and what expressions to make."


translate English day4_ar_T_747ed903:


    pl "And anyway..."


translate English day4_ar_T_7318e248:


    rv "Yes?"


translate English day4_ar_T_1e676c69:


    pl "N-Nothing, nothing! I said too much. Never mind!"


translate English day4_ar_T_18b7fce7:


    rv "You can tell me."


translate English day4_ar_T_3ed4ed70:


    pl "No, it's... I figured it out right as I said it."


translate English day4_ar_T_d61369e3:


    rv "If I was able to help, then I'm glad."


translate English day4_ar_T_21ca8360:


    nar "...And also, I still don't have enough information about her to stay at her side."


translate English day4_ar_T_5427efce:


    nar "Having such a seemingly attentive audience, I suddenly find myself blabbering away."


translate English day4_ar_T_616ae561:


    pl "I want your objective opinion on this. What kind of family are the Alternatas?"


translate English day4_ar_T_3d43053e:


    rv "The Alternatas?"


translate English day4_ar_T_b22a643d:


    pl "Yeah. You know a lot since you're an auxiliary bishop of the Academics Department, right?"


translate English day4_ar_T_b75f5d66:


    rv "Oh, no... You think too highly of me. "


translate English day4_ar_T_036bf3d0:


    rv "Hmm. Well, the profession of \"mage\" has been inherited through bloodlines for ages..."


translate English day4_ar_T_da2648bf:


    rv "There are many mage families, but they're all rooted in the same place. Did you know that much?"


translate English day4_ar_T_3a682340:


    pl "Yeah, I've heard that part before."


translate English day4_ar_T_dd7f246c:


    rv "Well, mages tend towards reliance on the divine power bestowed on them by their genes. "


translate English day4_ar_T_b6a668c1:


    rv "In essence, the stronger the bloodline, the more excellent the abilities you inherit."


translate English day4_ar_T_75191eb1:


    rv "The Alternatas are direct descendants of the mage family with the most surpassing bloodline of all."


translate English day4_ar_T_a49f70a8:


    pl "Huh, so that 1 and 3 stuff was family rankings... Now that you explain it, though, it seems really old-fashioned..."


translate English day4_ar_T_f44b5493:


    rv "The tradition has been passed down for a very long time, in fact. "


translate English day4_ar_T_fc1fdb79:


    rv "The issue is that mages don't stop at temples--their reach extends into politics as well."


translate English day4_ar_T_9524c0e7:


    rv "That situation is especially grave here on the northern continent--enough so that one could say the capital is currently ruled by dictatorial mages."


translate English day4_ar_T_04164996:


    pl "If you're even pulling out the word \"dictator,\" then people must not appreciate it much."


translate English day4_ar_T_e5dd87bc:


    rv "They don't. Many have been harmed by the various forms of discrmination advanced by mage supremacists. "


translate English day4_ar_T_6d1847e4:


    rv "The main examples of it are a person's number of stigmata and the color of their hair."


translate English day4_ar_T_100d5bdc:


    pl "Their hair color?"


translate English day4_ar_T_5be07b46:


    rv "Children born in barren lands tend to have less pigment because of it. Some say it has a direct link to one's level of sacred power."


translate English day4_ar_T_74cf7bc2:


    rv "To mages, black hair is considered sacred, while white hair is instead treated as the lowliest of the low."


translate English day4_ar_T_f2c76711:


    pl "Feels like I've heard that before... Discriminating based on hair color, though? Guess the capital really likes putting people in categories. "


translate English day4_ar_T_ae39320c:


    pl "It's like picking teams based on rock-paper-scissors."


translate English day4_ar_T_da21ccd8:


    rv "Well, they don't tend to have any other responsibilities keeping them busy."


translate English day4_ar_T_2fd7080a:


    nar "I was worried this would be awkward for us, but Lavien Rose seems like a more helpful person than I thought."


translate English day4_ar_T_37060f23:


    rv "The Alternata family originally had three siblings, but after an unfortunate accident, "


translate English day4_ar_T_db92ac14:


    rv "Erzsebet Alternata--the only one left--has taken leadership of them."


translate English day4_ar_T_65601a6c:


    rv "Excluding the cardinal, who normally never appears, you could say Lord Erzsebet holds the most powerful position in this nation."


translate English day4_ar_T_e17f53a0:


    pl "Whoa. Then his only daughter would be..."


translate English day4_ar_T_56982905:


    rv "Yes--the next family head once Lord Erzsebet steps down."


translate English day4_ar_T_7ab320ba:


    rv "Although things change if she becomes engaged before that..."


translate English day4_ar_T_a0dad038:


    nar "Engaged... The word comes up so suddenly it makes me shrink a little."


translate English day4_ar_T_333fb547:


    rv "That would explain why Lady Arne seems different from usual today."


translate English day4_ar_T_d2218e26:


    pl "Different how?"


translate English day4_ar_T_2d0983f8:


    rv "I've never seen her make a personal request of someone before."


translate English day4_ar_T_eb1e660c:


    pl "......"


translate English day4_ar_T_1fe5f6d8:


    rv "Frankly, I was astonished. Did you notice, little [na]?"


translate English day4_ar_T_11c2a02b:


    pl "No... I didn't think that far. She's asked me to do stuff a few times, like to stay at her side..."


translate English day4_ar_T_bcca4c16:


    rv "Then you'll have to get used to accepting the fact that someone likes you."


translate English day4_ar_T_e4bfdc99:


    pl "Is that really the type of guy I seem like to you?"


translate English day4_ar_T_5e470efa:


    rv "I think you would know that best, little [na]."


translate English day4_ar_T_914c914f:


    nar "Before I have a chance to think too deeply about it, the closed door swings open. Arnie is there, having calmed her breathing before entering."


translate English day4_ar_T_4f5c05d1:


    ar "I'm terribly sorry for making you wait like that."


translate English day4_ar_T_43bccc96:


    pl "Don't worry about it! It wasn't that long anyway."


translate English day4_ar_T_a7f603a9:


    rv "And anyway, we got to talking, so it went by in a flash."


translate English day4_ar_T_54632094:


    nar "Arnie takes a seat next to Lavi on the sofa across from me."


translate English day4_ar_T_9d034bc1:


    nar "There's a good head's worth of height difference between them, so I start getting confused about who I should look at."


translate English day4_ar_T_dac54ef6:


    pl "Seems like a rare sight for priests of the Magic and Academics Departments to be sitting right next to each other."


translate English day4_ar_T_3dfddbdd:


    rv "Oh, not at all. Our departments regularly exchange information, which means we have many opportunities to collaborate."


translate English day4_ar_T_f1817f4b:


    pl "Ah..."


translate English day4_ar_T_b4bd1d09:


    ar "It isn't just these two departments, either. All of the departments within the temple are working together."


translate English day4_ar_T_edd51c53:


    rv "Of course. The Academics Department does research based on information acquired by the Magic Department about the pestis,"


translate English day4_ar_T_cff8f9f3:


    rv "and then the Health Department can use that to implement effective healing measures faster."


translate English day4_ar_T_1c5fc01a:


    pl "And the Cleanup Department cleans up all the crap that the process creates... *sigh* I feel weirdly disappointed."


translate English day4_ar_T_17559cb7:


    pl "But I guess it wasn't originally its own thing, just the disposal team that used to be part of the Magic Department."


translate English day4_ar_T_70094814:


    ar "Please don't say that. The Cleanup Department is a vital area that supports the very life cycle of not only the temple but also the nation."


translate English day4_ar_T_56d44e06:


    rv "Without the Cleanup Department supporting everything else behind the scenes, the coordination we have would be impossible."


translate English day4_ar_T_417cc512:


    pl "I guess maybe, but... Well, anyway, it seems like communication is actually pretty important at the temple, huh?"


translate English day4_ar_T_174c9d14:


    rv "Communication between groups has been treated as crucial for a very long time. "


translate English day4_ar_T_abf25730:


    rv "In fact, we hold goodwill competitions to foster exchange between departments."


translate English day4_ar_T_5e8c28d9:


    rv "We do it every year, where all four departments compete against one another."


translate English day4_ar_T_f193b973:


    pl "I didn't know we had events like that here."


translate English day4_ar_T_b558508c:


    rv "Oh, but of course. The priests who work here live restricted lives in many ways, so they need a chance to, well, vent. "


translate English day4_ar_T_f1bb8bfa:


    rv "Otherwise, they wouldn't be able to keep working here for years on end."


translate English day4_ar_T_0fd809c9:


    pl "I find myself kind of surprised to hear you say the word \"vent.\""


translate English day4_ar_T_d0f0646c:


    rv "Hehe."


translate English day4_ar_T_cf1c9ccd:


    ar "The goodwill competitions are certainly done with an emphasis on promoting interdepartmental exchange..."


translate English day4_ar_T_1ccb4d98:


    ar "But in many cases, the Cleanup Department won't participate because of their significant workload and the Health Department can only participate in certain events."


translate English day4_ar_T_4daf7e56:


    ar "It has devolved into a rivalry between the Magic and Academics Departments."


translate English day4_ar_T_283f8f9c:


    pl "Ah... Right. I figured."


translate English day4_ar_T_da969c1d:


    rv "Little [na], won't you be in the Magic Department by the time the next goodwill competition is held?"


translate English day4_ar_T_5653b0b2:


    pl "I don't know... It sounds fun, but I wouldn't be able to participate in very much, would I?"


translate English day4_ar_T_613b26df:


    nar "The two girls stay silent for a moment, blinking at me."


translate English day4_ar_T_277c743e:


    ar "Why would you think that? I believe we would make good use of your abilities in the Magic-Academics Battle..."


translate English day4_ar_T_f702be4d:


    rv "Indeed! The Academics-Magic Battle is the perfect stage on which to make your abilities known to the temple."


translate English day4_ar_T_51b69c48:


    pl "Hmm... I'm happy for the flattery, but I guess I can't quite wrap my head around it."


translate English day4_ar_T_8f245f62:


    ar "Then why not accompany me in the training room?"


translate English day4_ar_T_91985132:


    pl "Now, I don't think we need to go that far!"


translate English day4_ar_T_8a74c0a5:


    ar "This may be a very selfish desire, but I'd very much like you to stand with us during the Magic-Academics Battle." with sshake


translate English day4_ar_T_b4fcbe2b:


    nar "It's very hard for me to say no to her brave attitude, so I'm the one who shuts up this time."


translate English day4_ar_T_6ec67906:


    nar "But on the verge of awkward silence descending once again, Lavien sets herself and says:"


translate English day4_ar_T_26e67c49:


    rv "You mean the Academics-Magic Battle, yes?"


translate English day4_ar_T_014f6461:


    pl "I'll, uh, I'll think about it... Right! If the goodwill competition is a yearly event, does that mean there are others?"


translate English day4_ar_T_e1f3f7ab:


    rv "If we're considering other major events, there is the Holy Night Festival held at the end of the year."


translate English day4_ar_T_bcd271c8:


    rv "It's a festival we hold in the capital to celebrate the holy night when our Lord was born."


translate English day4_ar_T_13ad32ba:


    pl "If it's a temple thing, then why does the whole capital do it?"


translate English day4_ar_T_39a9a4fd:


    ar "In essence, the temple is the focal point of the capital."


translate English day4_ar_T_1e223926:


    ar "The main job of the Magic Department is to maintain the barrier around the capital."


translate English day4_ar_T_dcbfa039:


    ar "The Holy Night Festival strengthens this barrier, and until dawn breaks, the priests all rest."


translate English day4_ar_T_433fed09:


    pl "Rest? Does that mean we could leave the temple?"


translate English day4_ar_T_57480c99:


    ar "It does indeed."


translate English day4_ar_T_656fb45e:


    rv "Although I would stay behind to guard the library."


translate English day4_ar_T_64862915:


    nar "After dropping that uncharacteristically casual but meaningful remark, Lavien abruptly stands up."


translate English day4_ar_T_ee097c91:


    rv "Now then, I should be on my way."


translate English day4_ar_T_e1ae3166:


    pl "Already? Didn't you come here to see Enoch?"


translate English day4_ar_T_3ba72d72:


    rv "I can't leave the library unattended for very long and I might run into him on the way back."


translate English day4_ar_T_d9c7a167:


    ar "I'm sorry I was unable to offer you much of anything."


translate English day4_ar_T_cd563a99:


    rv "No, not at all. I shouldn't have barged in here without notice. Next time, I will come quietly and bearing gifts."


translate English day4_ar_T_82501cbf:


    nar "I'm pretty sure she's talking to Arnie, but she's looking over at me."


translate English day4_ar_T_0de4e93f:


    rv "Please enjoy your time together. Ah, and come visit the library every once in a while, too."


translate English day4_ar_T_6a4c792f:


    pl "Sure. Take care."


translate English day4_ar_T_fb6c45d8:


    nar "Just like the first time I met her, the priest left as suddenly as she arrived. The room fell silent without her continuously driving the conversation."


translate English day4_ar_T_a47d9d22:


    nar "I start to get nervous. What kind of thing do I usually talk about with her, again?"


translate English day4_ar_T_0be3e930:


    ar "...Until the Holy Night ends and we welcome in a new dawn."


translate English day4_ar_T_30e8f071:


    nar "Perhaps picking up on how I feel, she begins talking first. "


translate English day4_ar_T_3626f864:


    nar "The soft tones of her voice and her comfortable expression don't seem to share any of my discomfort or tension."


translate English day4_ar_T_5645aec6:


    ar "When a priest leaves the temple to go on a journey, they return to the homeland from whence they came."


translate English day4_ar_T_bb891456:


    ar "Would you mind telling me a little about your home, Brother [na2]?"


translate English day4_ar_T_4ff1e501:


    pl "My home? Well, sure, but it's not that interesting... What did you want to know?"


translate English day4_ar_T_3fbcb234:


    ar "Why don't we start with the flora and fauna native to it? "


translate English day4_ar_T_bcbfb4f0:


    ar "And then how the seasons change, how the water tastes, what it feels like when the air tickles your skin..."


translate English day4_ar_T_88fac97e:


    ar "I want to know everything about the place in which you were raised."


translate English day4_ar_T_9c95aca4:


    pl "Oh... Sure. Here in the capital, you can always hear merchants shouting or machines running,"


translate English day4_ar_T_1079bccd:


    pl "but back where I used to live, you could only hear one thing at this time of year: cicadas."


translate English day4_ar_T_701250e4:


    pl "Cicadas are these really loud bugs, but they have really short lifespans. They cry at the top of their lungs for a little while, then completely die out."


translate English day4_ar_T_0f8a0d2c:


    pl "When you can't hear the cicadas anymore, that's when autumn starts."


translate English day4_ar_T_b8b0bcb7:


    nar "That sweltering, humid smell, the slippery sensation of the bug repellent the adults would put on my skin, the sounds of the fish swimming in the river..."


translate English day4_ar_T_435da0b9:


    nar "Memories of those days come back to me after being away for so long."


translate English day4_ar_T_1c509299:


    nar "I tell her about them, almost like I'm delivering a monologue. I would have thought it would bore people, "


translate English day4_ar_T_6dbd3049:


    nar "but Arnie actually seems like she's listening."


translate English day4_ar_T_7b457a22:


    pl "...And in the summer, when the overgrown weeds would get tripped, the fragrant olives would bloom, telling us autumn was here."


translate English day4_ar_T_5a888ac5:


    pl "I was never very interested in plants and fragrant olives have a strong smell, so I didn't like them very much..."


translate English day4_ar_T_e443c0e4:


    pl "But now that I look back on it, those flowers were kind of like you. They bloom off their tree branches and go straight up towards the sun."


translate English day4_ar_T_32df913c:


    ar "I'm honored that you would see such a powerful a memory in me."


translate English day4_ar_T_5efb1792:


    pl "Heh, I'd like to show you them sometime! But that's enough about me. What was it like when you were growing up?"


translate English day4_ar_T_c0d60777:


    ar "Well... I was brought up in our family estate from a young age, where I was educated."


translate English day4_ar_T_efa801fb:


    ar "I knew things existed outside the estate, but until coming to this temple, I never saw them."


translate English day4_ar_T_f0567d3d:


    pl "Ever?"


translate English day4_ar_T_3edf95d1:


    ar "Well, save for Enoch bringing me all sorts of flowers."


translate English day4_ar_T_32143eaa:


    ar "Ever since coming to the mansion, he liked to play outside. The flowers would tell me of the changing seasons."


translate English day4_ar_T_aaa2ca63:


    pl "Really? Guess he's always been a hopeless romantic, then. I wouldn't have done it quite like that, though."


translate English day4_ar_T_f7646645:


    ar "What would you have done, if you had been in his shoes?"


translate English day4_ar_T_d854f404:


    pl "I'd probably want to surprise you once in a while. "


translate English day4_ar_T_88b06023:


    pl "There's pretty stuff all over the place outside, but there's just as much weird stuff. Must have been boring looking at flowers every day, right?"


translate English day4_ar_T_ee6201df:


    ar "Boring... Hmm. Heh heh... That does seem fun in its own right. Thank you for informing me of a new way to have fun."


translate English day4_ar_T_7187c775:


    pl "Don't mention it. If you're having fun, I'm having fun, ha ha ha!"


translate English day4_ar_T_6d012744:


    ar "And you'll be able to see the sights of your home during this year's rest."


translate English day4_ar_T_63e9b6a9:


    pl "...Actually, I wouldn't go back, even if I had the chance. "


translate English day4_ar_T_d28e6225:


    pl "It was fun remembering the day-to-day life there, but I value my freedom over my home village."


translate English day4_ar_T_b1708dae:


    pl "I left of my own accord, so I don't want to go back again. I can't go back."


translate English day4_ar_T_1e47bc41:


    ar "A place you left of your own accord..."


translate English day4_ar_T_575a5a23:


    pl "Have you ever felt like everything was too restricting? "


translate English day4_ar_T_ff234734:


    pl "Like instead of listening to other people all the time, you wanted to try just...leaving the capital?"


translate English day4_ar_T_c1423c22:


    pl "I want to do that! There's so many things I'd want to show you."


translate English day4_ar_T_e425c9cd:


    ar "I am incredibly grateful for how considerate you are. "


translate English day4_ar_T_378335b5:


    ar "But I have never once considered my lack of outside knowledge to be unfortunate in any way."


translate English day4_ar_T_b2009ee9:


    ar "God has granted me my position as the eldest daughter of the Alternatas--along with my duty to protect them."


translate English day4_ar_T_264d6911:


    ar "I cannot think of a greater honor."


translate English day4_ar_T_1871d514:


    nar "I remember what Lavien said to me before: \"Then you'll have to get used to accepting the fact that someone likes you.\""


translate English day4_ar_T_45ef2724:


    pl "Yeah, but that's exactly what I don't get... Haaah..."


translate English day4_ar_T_d500aab1:


    ar "I'm sorry. I must seem like quite the boring woman."


translate English day4_ar_T_86c87121:


    pl "What? No, I think you're totally interesting. And even if you were boring, I don't think that would be your fault."


translate English day4_ar_T_fb453f9a:


    nar "The other mages can't do this for her, but I can do it--"


translate English day4_ar_T_b2328d28:


    nar "broaden her perspective. I know of so many things that would shock and amaze her."


translate English day4_ar_T_55b05bf0:


    nar "Like cicada shells. The creatures would probably look so strange to someone who never saw the outside and only heard about classy things."


translate English day4_ar_T_cc0cdeeb:


    nar "Just imagining her beautiful eyes widening in surprise gives me a fluttering feeling inside my chest."


translate English day4_ar_T_46acb395:


    nar "And there's more--cats that can slip right out of your grasp, the two nuts inside a sharp chestnut."


translate English day4_ar_T_29112d73:


    nar "This world is full of things you'll only understand by seeing them personally. Just talking about them would never be enough."


translate English day4_ar_T_1b5ec136:


    pl "You know, if you're really set on accepting me as part of your family, you're going to want to brace yourself."


translate English day4_ar_T_53deb184:


    ar "Oh, I can assure you that I am fully prepared."


translate English day4_rs_T_370b3619:


    br "\n Lavien Rose is someone who can be seen from time to time during our days living at the temple.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_rs_T_41e00a4a:


    extend " I don't know how it is in other departments, but in the Cleanup Department, at least, that's how it is.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_rs_T_3972221b:


    extend " Responsible for dealing with any and all kinds of garbage, the department makes use of a variety of machines.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_rs_T_4f42d255:


    extend " The sight of someone placing a bag crawling with small flies to the side and turning on a machine with roughly honed motions, all in a dimly lit storehouse, is an unusual one you'd normally only see in this department.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_rs_T_bc2b4290:


    extend " Every day, the rusted machine runs, producing a constant, frightful roar--and sometimes, it stops abruptly.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_rs_T_26d425bd:


    extend "When it stops, an uneducated priest of the processing team kicks it and yells."


translate English day4_rs_T_8be44dbd:



    nvl clear
    br "\n\"Call someone from the Academics Department!\"{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_rs_T_270f89b3:


    extend "\nThe \"someone\" is always the same person--Lavien Rose. {w}{nw}"


translate English day4_rs_T_15afb3e9:


    extend "The tiny priest always runs over carrying a bag larger than her body {w}{nw}"


translate English day4_rs_T_466bd414:


    extend "and wearing thick leather gloves and goggles, then glues herself to the worn-out machine. {w}{nw}"


translate English day4_rs_T_b82bfeec:


    extend "She leaves the storehouse a little while later, grinning happily, face covered in soot--{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_rs_T_3cbcc096:


    extend "ushered out by the bold, smooth sounds of the machine.{w}{nw}"


translate English day4_rs_T_d2e93fbd:


    extend "\n And even when everyone is busy, she always remembers to be polite and greet those she sees, making her well-liked. {w}{nw}"


translate English day4_rs_T_bf9fd82e:


    extend "To this temple, that is who Lavien Rose is."


translate English day4_rs_T_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day4_rs_T_a08b2a50:


    nar "I decide to adjust my destination and enter the library again."


translate English day4_rs_T_834b6575:


    nar "Last time I just felt creeped out, like someone was watching me the whole time. But after the accident, I've started to get the bigger picture."


translate English day4_rs_T_c287cdee:


    nar "They're probably hiding, watching me right now. "


translate English day4_rs_T_78eff3e8:


    nar "No bishops come to speak to me directly, though--maybe because they'd seen me speak to the bishop directly."


translate English day4_rs_T_5581d3eb:


    nar "After glancing around and carefully opening the door, a soft, fluffy zabuton hits me in the face."


translate English day4_rs_T_63097482:


    nar "I push it away only to see a girl hoisting another cushion, ready to throw it."


translate English day4_rs_T_74993d20:


    rs "You didn't listen to Rose's warning! Outsider! Outsider! GET OUT!!!" with sshake


translate English day4_rs_T_f4dae0f1:


    pl "Hey, wait! Don't throw a fit!"


translate English day4_rs_T_8dab2378:


    nar "Given how quiet the library always is, sounds like our fighting carry pretty far. "


translate English day4_rs_T_048ff1f2:


    nar "I hurry and close the door first as she throws the zabuton at me, then some dolls. They hit me in the back and shoulders. Will she go for the books next?"


translate English day4_rs_T_57573615:


    pl "Keep it down! This is a library!"


translate English day4_rs_T_ff99590a:


    rs "This is Rose's space!"


translate English day4_rs_T_5aa984bd:


    pl "A space that's part of the library! Let's just calm down, alright?"


translate English day4_rs_T_7d32d1ac:


    rs "[na] of the Cleanup Department. You have failed to obey my warnings twice now. You are an outsider. You are not permitted to remain here."


translate English day4_rs_T_627cdce5:


    pl "That's not actually true. I got direct permission for this today."


translate English day4_rs_T_570f2cd1:


    rs "I fail to understand...?"


translate English day4_rs_T_4c762afa:


    nar "Rose suddenly stops, her arms lifted in a stance that implies she's about to charge me. "


translate English day4_rs_T_ae1a0377:


    nar "I basically get what's going on, but needing to treat the same person as two different people and tell this one what the other already said felt really weird."


translate English day4_rs_T_0cbb8091:


    pl "I know you probably don't remember, but... This afternoon, the assistant bishop of the Academics Department, Lavien Rose, talked to me directly. She told me to take good care of you."


translate English day4_rs_T_aeff66e8:


    pl "Meaning I'm not an outsider anymore. I'm an insider now!"


translate English day4_rs_T_3ecdee97:


    rs "......"


translate English day4_rs_T_1fdc8eec:


    nar "Having thrown everything nearby at me, she completely stops moving."


translate English day4_rs_T_a12a179a:


    nar "There isn't a shred of confusion or surprise on her face. She looks blank, like all the emotions drained out of her. "


translate English day4_rs_T_ae6ecd7c:


    nar "Definitely seems like a totally different person than the candid, outspoken one before."


translate English day4_rs_T_0cce7182:


    nar "It's so strange how a person can seem so different just by changing their expressions and manner of speaking."


translate English day4_rs_T_f06721f5:


    rs "Oh."


translate English day4_rs_T_ef202537:


    nar "I expected suspicious resistance, but she says only that before trudging over to me"


translate English day4_rs_T_225fc168:


    nar "and picking up the nearby zabutons. That only serves to make me more perplexed."


translate English day4_rs_T_b2c1192b:


    pl "Wait, you're not gonna start asking questions or anything?"


translate English day4_rs_T_80505bfe:


    rs "Why would I? Rose understands perfectly. Lavien Rose's decisions are absolute."


translate English day4_rs_T_f62b6112:


    rs "Hence, if she came to the answer that you are trustworthy and valid, then Rose can only follow it."


translate English day4_rs_T_d8c05df0:


    pl "I mean, I didn't exactly want to argue, but... Seeing how, uh, obedient you can be is really throwing me off... "


translate English day4_rs_T_0747faa9:


    pl "You don't even have any guarantee that what I say is true. What were you going to do if I was lying?"


translate English day4_rs_T_dad0b040:


    nar "As soon as I stop speaking, she comes right up to me and brings her face close to mine."


translate English day4_rs_T_695d73cf:


    nar "The man reflected in her pitch-black eyes wears a surprised expression. "


translate English day4_rs_T_23c5bced:


    nar "The large eyes remain open, unblinking. They're strangely terrifying, like two very deep, unending holes."


translate English day4_rs_T_e3da86c3:


    rs "Speaking the truth requires courage. Telling a lie requires just as much resolve."


translate English day4_rs_T_fd774412:


    rs "On this point, you don't seem to be lying."


translate English day4_rs_T_b5294864:


    pl "...You can tell all that?"


translate English day4_rs_T_686feaf2:


    rs "For the most part."


translate English day4_rs_T_3908f986:


    nar "She puts a zabuton back down, lies down on it, and picks up her still-open book. "


translate English day4_rs_T_2ff531db:


    nar "Her body slides and sinks into the expensive pillow. It's such a carefree thing to do with a guest in the room that "


translate English day4_rs_T_f6a5f1f6:


    nar "I start to feel awkward just standing there."


translate English day4_rs_T_11638924:


    pl "Can I read the books here too?"


translate English day4_rs_T_c4468fbc:


    rs "...Studying?"


translate English day4_rs_T_9629f577:


    pl "Something like that."


translate English day4_rs_T_fa51e85e:


    rs "You may read the books in the fourth row from the top. Rose gives her permission."


translate English day4_rs_T_f371b7f7:


    pl "So cold..."


translate English day4_rs_T_32aa879b:


    nar "She was so angry at me before. Now she won't even look in my direction."


translate English day4_rs_T_cc1fdefd:


    nar "Without a word, I take out a book and start to read. It's been a long time since I last opened a book for myself--especially a children's story."


translate English day4_rs_T_9fc80bd7:


    pl "If you don't have anything better to do, then help me read this."


translate English day4_rs_T_8b3465f9:


    nar "No answer. Why is everyone so insistent on ignoring me? It's so annoying."


translate English day4_rs_T_48da05f5:


    pl "Hey! Rose. Help a guy out here."


translate English day4_rs_T_6601aa08:


    rs "Mm?"


translate English day4_rs_T_1ee4d4a6:


    nar "Her next reaction is nothing like what I anticipated."


translate English day4_rs_T_e521de13:


    nar "Rose--whose face was hidden behind her book in an expression of disdain towards me--suddenly does a one-eighty and widens her eyes at me just about as far as they'll go."


translate English day4_rs_T_070cd246:


    rs "Did you just ask Rose for help?"


translate English day4_rs_T_e87a4cc8:


    pl "Wh-What...?"


translate English day4_rs_T_05088dc7:


    rs "Does that mean you require Rose's assistance?"


translate English day4_rs_T_a734cf3d:


    pl "Well, yes, but..."


translate English day4_rs_T_0fdb0822:


    nar "As soon as she hears that, she pulls herself into an upright sitting position and starts hitting her legs and the floor. "


translate English day4_rs_T_96b364a6:


    nar "You wouldn't be able to tell it from her face, but she seems pretty excited about something."


translate English day4_rs_T_ca3c635c:


    rs "What do you require?"


translate English day4_rs_T_2a004506:


    pl "Why are you suddenly so eager? It's making me uncomfortable..."


translate English day4_rs_T_9d920845:


    rs "Nobody ever asks Rose for help but Rose is always prepared to help others."


translate English day4_rs_T_303e5d27:


    nar "With her attitude changing drastically by the minute, I have no idea how I'm even supposed to respond to her."


translate English day4_rs_T_92440fc5:


    pl "That's probably because everyone else is trying to be considerate, since they know what's going on with you."


translate English day4_rs_T_13395a96:


    rs "Considerate? Why?"


translate English day4_rs_T_9a40caf6:


    pl "Well, you're kind of like a sick patient at the moment, so..."


translate English day4_rs_T_10a7676f:


    rs "Rose is not sick. She neither has any illness nor does it hurt anywhere."


translate English day4_rs_T_2b141c50:


    rs "Rose's mind and body are all in a perfectly good state, and are suitable enough to help others."


translate English day4_rs_T_3a2a29ed:


    pl "I get why you feel like that, but... This is hard. Anyway, you'll help me out, right?"


translate English day4_rs_T_70c9d772:


    rs "Yes."


translate English day4_rs_T_d7b1d48d:


    pl "Okay, then first, this part."


translate English day4_rs_T_a5e764b6:


    rs "Mm."


translate English day4_rs_T_0141e70a:


    nar "I point to the word with my finger, placing the book in front of her, though the letters are upside-down. "


translate English day4_rs_T_f6c5d926:


    nar "I catch a whiff of the library's flowers from her, too."


translate English day4_rs_T_bb8dd27c:


    nar "Is everyone in the Academics Department like this? I really have no idea, since the greasy odor of corpses always lingers around the processing team."


translate English day4_rs_T_f5c56814:


    rs "\"Susceptible.\""


translate English day4_rs_T_8c7724d1:


    pl "Wait, not \"suspectible\"?"


translate English day4_rs_T_92b57a64:


    rs "The letters are in a different order."


translate English day4_rs_T_4116f1b1:


    pl "This is hard..."


translate English day4_rs_T_5b5aa252:


    rs "[na] of the Cleanup Department, I request to know how much you read on average."


translate English day4_rs_T_3fcd5215:


    pl "Well, not much, that's for sure. Stories made up by other people just don't interest me..."


translate English day4_rs_T_403e3fee:


    rs "Then what do you like?"


translate English day4_rs_T_fc53ae79:


    pl "Stories like these, I guess. The kind where it's worth going and verifying it for yourself. Haven't you ever thought about that?"


translate English day4_rs_T_90753c99:


    rs "Verifying?"


translate English day4_rs_T_bf3cdcbb:


    pl "For example, if there was a flower that bloomed early in the morning, but wilted at night, wouldn't you want to see it at least once?"


translate English day4_rs_T_f0ca274e:


    rs "No. Rose has no interest in flowers."


translate English day4_rs_T_906fae38:


    pl "I mean, that was just an example."


translate English day4_rs_T_95fbe112:


    rs "Do you always think that way? Flowers are simply the reproductive organs of plants."


translate English day4_rs_T_7edd929f:


    pl "I think you're misunderstanding. I'm not exactly a flower fanatic, here..."


translate English day4_rs_T_472be9d2:


    rs "You're not?"


translate English day4_rs_T_fb06b0f8:


    pl "Well, no, but I never think of stuff in extreme ways like you do."


translate English day4_rs_T_0e97143d:


    pl "I'm surprised you can say that, given you're holed up in this room that smells like flowers all the time..."


translate English day4_rs_T_f8d4633f:


    rs "Some say flower scents are meant to deceive others, not for pure decoration."


translate English day4_rs_T_45a96db5:


    pl "Wh-Who would say something like that...?"


translate English day4_rs_T_cd1aa262:


    rs "Lady Evelynn."


translate English day4_rs_T_508f59be:


    pl "Yeah, I can see it..."


translate English day4_rs_T_3b59081f:


    nar "The library may be downstairs and underground, but she burns incense inside it anyway. It's to draw people here, like a Venus flytrap waiting for a bug to fall into it."


translate English day4_rs_T_5dae44b2:


    nar "Everything that woman says and does gives me the creeps."


translate English day4_rs_T_54cb6b90:


    pl "Then you haven't ever even wanted to go outside?"


translate English day4_rs_T_a02e273a:


    rs "This is the only space where Rose is permitted to be."


translate English day4_rs_T_98122291:


    pl "But nobody set that rule for you."


translate English day4_rs_T_96c2cf76:


    rs "Outside is neither enjoyable nor beneficial, so Rose doesn't feel the need to leave."


translate English day4_rs_T_f55023f3:


    pl "Don't come crying to me if mold starts to grow on you from staying cooped up in here all the time."


translate English day4_rs_T_4f0c6ee4:


    rs "Rose requests further details."


translate English day4_rs_T_4ebb4ec6:


    pl "I mean you'll stop being able to move. Forever."


translate English day4_rs_T_e4e2e129:


    rs "That would be an issue."


translate English day4_rs_T_d44a6b8f:


    pl "It would, right? Man, why do I have to be the one to explain this..."


translate English day4_rs_T_f4b742ea:


    rs "Observation suggests that curiosity makes up a considerable portion of the instincts defining your personality. What are you searching for?"


translate English day4_rs_T_2a44f0e8:


    pl "I'm not searching for anything in particular right now. If I had to say, I'm sort of looking for something that makes me want to search for it."


translate English day4_rs_T_9b85fdd0:


    pl "Living life without a purpose is boring. Not worth it to waste time like that, is it?"


translate English day4_rs_T_ed50c3d7:


    rs "Hmm."


translate English day4_rs_T_d364279e:


    nar "Now that you said 'personality' and 'instincts,' I'm feeling curious about something new."


translate English day4_rs_T_4d309576:


    pl "You don't remember anything that happened today, do you?"


translate English day4_rs_T_6601aa08_1:


    rs "Mm?"


translate English day4_rs_T_da094944:


    pl "I'm curious about how your brain works. Based on what you said before, you seem to remember the bishop."


translate English day4_rs_T_805ed8fa:


    nar "Rose is silent for a few moments. Her expression is too inorganic to know if she's thinking about it or avoiding answering."


translate English day4_rs_T_83d2fd49:


    rs "Not applicable."


translate English day4_rs_T_2b1569e1:


    pl "Oh. Well, that's unfortunate. Though I guess if you'd remembered, you wouldn't have attacked me..."


translate English day4_rs_T_ca39906e:


    rs "Are you finished asking questions?"


translate English day4_rs_T_26485e83:


    pl "Uh, sure. Seems like I won't be able to get any answers out of you anyway."


translate English day4_rs_T_32d02a8d:


    rs "Will you not read the book?"


translate English day4_rs_T_29779076:


    pl "Hmm... I guess I'll keep on reading until I go back."


translate English day4_rs_T_6e9c6e10:


    nar "It's already time to grant the request I received in the library. I've read many books, but I don't like them much."


translate English day4_rs_T_cc482a4f:


    nar "Especially children's books. I get frustrated with how smoothly the stories go--it's just hard to believe them. "


translate English day4_rs_T_611f27ce:


    nar "She doesn't seem to feel that way, though. She remains right next to me, her eyes glued to her book."


translate English day4_rs_T_e769e034:


    nar "I try several times to focus on my own book to keep myself in line with her, but in the end I can't help but yawn."


translate English day4_rs_T_2507863f:


    pl "You seem like you're having fun."


translate English day4_rs_T_6601aa08_2:


    rs "Pardon?"


translate English day4_rs_T_835693ca:


    pl "You read the same books every day all by yourself, but it has to get boring at some point."


translate English day4_rs_T_791153fb:


    rs "Books are not meant to be read as a way to pursue enjoyment."


translate English day4_rs_T_f34ff45c:


    rs "Books were created to give as many people as possible a way to tell their stories. "


translate English day4_rs_T_df4abed2:


    rs "Thus, books exist to increase the amount of information an individual possesses. In fact, you are currently using that book's information to learn your letters."


translate English day4_rs_T_2774db1f:


    pl "But if it's just to get more information into your head, why read them over and over? Isn't that a contradiction? You just want some way to pass the time, don't you?"


translate English day4_rs_T_05d22c51:


    rs "This is Rose's job."


translate English day4_rs_T_5106e0b3:


    pl "Gaining information?"


translate English day4_rs_T_41ea9fcb:


    rs "Indeed."


translate English day4_rs_T_3ba1eabc:


    pl "Sounds like a job you'd do at a children's school. Is it some kind of education? Like how you can train your brain even while you're asleep?"


translate English day4_rs_T_6601aa08_3:


    rs "?"


translate English day4_rs_T_8cd806f5:


    pl "Well, anyway, it seems like you're having fun, so I'm glad."


translate English day4_rs_T_c0791ef5:


    rs "It looks... like Rose is having fun?"


translate English day4_rs_T_8f1cafc3:


    pl "Yeah. To me, anyway."


translate English day4_rs_T_c60633a7:


    rs "Does that mean Rose is enjoying this time spent with you?"


translate English day4_rs_T_3e4da7ee:


    pl "Wh-What are you asking me that far? Don't make it awkward... What do you think?"


translate English day4_rs_T_2de5651a:


    rs "I don't know... What is fun?"


